title: rolled beef log
directions: Blend together beef, eggs, bread crumbs, oregano, garlic salt, cayenne and 1/2 can tomato sauce with onions.
Mix well.
Pat meat into a 16 x 10-inch rectangle on wax paper or aluminum foil.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar in mixing bowl until light and fluffy at medium speed.
Add eggs; beat 2 more minutes.
Add bananas; beat 2 more minutes.
Sift together flour, baking soda, powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla. Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into 2 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut on each layer. Bake in 375° oven 25 to 30 minutes or until cakes test done.
Cool in pans on rack 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on racks.

title: cheese and chili cornbread
directions: In large bowl, mix the first 5 ingredients.
In medium bowl, beat cheese, corn, chilies, onion, eggs, milk and butter until blended.
Stir into flour mixture.
Put batter in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: "Tender quick" cook broccoli; drain and arrange broccoli in buttered casserole dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise, juice, cheese and pimento; spoon over broccoli and top with crackers and nuts.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.

title: chicken with peppers
directions: Brown the chickens under the broiler.
Place chicken in medium skillet.
Add the onion, wine, salt and pepper.
Cook until wine is reduced to half, then add the tomatoes.
Saute for several minutes in saucepan the olive oil, garlic and green peppers.
Add chicken; cook until chicken is fork-tender.
Place in bed of noodles or pasta.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and chips.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put the cheese and chips on top.
Bake in 350° oven 30 minutes.
Can be made the day before.
Refrigerate, then bake.

title: hamburger cookies and fries
directions: Lay vanilla wafer, rounded side down; drop small amount of yellow frosting on top.
Gently push a mint cookie on top.
Put red frosting on top of mint cookie; add some green coconut.
Take second vanilla wafer and put small amount of frosting inside and gently press onto coconut.
Brush top with egg whites and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Put in cupcake paper and add shoestring potatoes on the side.

title: veg-all chicken pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Spoon into pie crust.
Top with other crust.
Cut slit in top.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.

title: crab dip divine
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Chill.
Nice served in a pineapple shell with crisp crackers.

title: mexican rice casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Add water, tomato sauce, salt, chili powder, Picante Sauce and rice.
Heat to boiling and cover. Simmer 20 minutes.
Spoon 1/2 of mixture in 2 qt casserole dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cheese and bacon.
Add remaining meat mixture and top with cheese and brown.
Bake at 450 F for 15 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
You can microwave this meal also.

title: picadillo soup
directions: Saute garlic with onions and tomatoes.
Add 2 bouillon cubes. Saute well on medium heat.
Add meat and potatoes with about 1/4 cup water.
Let boil; continue adding water to make soup consistency.

title: divinity
directions: Cook until you can spin a thread or drop a small amount in cold water and make a hard ball.
Beat 2 egg whites stiff.
Pour syrup into eggs, a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Put a pecan half on each candy.

title: mound cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine sweetened condensed milk and cream of coconut.
Pour over cake.
Punch holes in cake so mixture will soak in.
When cake cools, spread whipped topping over top and sprinkle with bag of coconut.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: sour cream candy
directions: Combine the sugar and sour cream; cook to soft ball stage. Remove from heat.
Add salt and butter; beat until mixture begins to grain.
Stir in vanilla and chopped nuts.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: arroz con leche
directions: Bring water to a boil. Add rice, cinnamon and raisins.
Simmer 20 minutes. Add the milk until it warms. Serve. Add sugar to taste and milk, if desired.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs.
Beat well.
Combine baking soda and buttermilk.
Combine flour, dates, candy, nuts and coconut.
Beat well.
Be sure all are coated with flour so they will not stick together.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Pour juice off pickles and save.
Take pickles out of jar. After cutting off stems, cut pickles into about 3/4-inch chunks and return to jar.
Add sugar to jar and fill jar with juice that was originally in pickles.
Shake until sugar dissolves. Refrigerate and shake one or two times a day for four days.

title: easy chocolate candy
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter, mix in sugar.
Line bottom of cookie pan with saltines.
Pour butter/sugar mixture over crackers.
Bake at 350° for approximately 15 minutes, or until brown and bubbly.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle on Nestle morsels (they will melt).
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Mix well and spread over cool crust.
Combine chocolate pudding with cold milk and pour over above.
When pudding has set, cover with Cool Whip and chill.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add other ingredients except Rice Krispies and pecans.
Mix thoroughly, then add Rice Krispies.
Put in refrigerator to harden, then make into round cookies and put pecans on top.
Bake at 350° until brown, about 15 minutes.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 stick melted oleo and press into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill for 2 hours.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix flour, salt, soda and sugar.
Add shortening, sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Beat this mixture for three minutes.
Fold in strawberries.
Pour into greased square baking dish and bake at 250° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream, ice cream or strawberry sauce.

title: hidden valley ranch quesadilla
directions: Blend together the above ingredients except tortillas and vegetable oil.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Spread cooled mixture over 5 tortillas.
Cover with remaining 5 tortillas.
Brush tortillas with vegetable oil.
On a baking sheet, broil until golden brown.
Turn and repeat process until cheese is melted.

title: chicken or turkey dressing casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bone and cut into chunks.
Place 1/2 chicken in greased baking dish.
Spread with half of the chopped onion and half of dressing mixture.
Combine both cans of soup and broth or water.
Pour 1/2 soup mixture over dressing, then repeat layers with remaining chicken, dressing and soup.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: louisiana dirty rice casserole
directions: Season beef and put into a 3-quart microwave casserole dish with cover.
Add next three ingredients and cover.
Microwave on High (700 watts) for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir to crumble beef.
Stir in pimento and cans of soup.
Add rice and seasoning to taste.
Mix well.
Microwave on High 5 minutes, then on Medium-low (350 watts) for an additional 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir.
Microwave on Medium-low about 10 minutes longer or until liquid is absorbed and rice is done.
Remove and let sit 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: colorful fried rice
directions: Spread sesame seed in a small frying pan over medium heat. Cook, shaking pan often, until seed is golden (about 2 minutes); set aside.
Prepare remaining ingredients before you begin cooking.
Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a wok or wide frying pan over high heat.
Add carrots; stir-fry (cook, stirring constantly) for 1 minute.
Mix in onion, garlic and green pepper; stir-fry for 1 minute more.
Add more oil as needed.
Add zucchini and mushrooms; stir-fry until all vegies are just tender-crisp (about 2 more minutes).
Mix in bean sprouts and rice; cook, stirring, until heated through.

title: easy 7-layer dip
directions: In serving dish, layer the ingredients.
Chill and serve with Fritos scoops corn chips.

title: mom's zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Pour 1 1/2-inches of water in bottom of a double boiler.
In top half, place chips and melt. Add honey or syrup.
Stir.
Now add flakes and mix well. Add raisins and mix.
Take off heat and drop onto wax paper.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: blueberry coffee cake
directions: Cut first 4 ingredients together with 1/2 cup oleo.
Add to milk and beaten eggs.
Add blueberries and bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Put powdered sugar frosting on top.

title: spinach pie
directions: You will need one 8 1/2-inch aluminum pie pan.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak into bite size pieces. In skillet brown steak in 2 Tbsp. of oil. Pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients, cover, simmer 1 1/2 hours. Stir often.

title: apricot bars
directions: Beat softened butter with sugar.
Mix in soda, flour, oats and salt.
Brush an 8 x 12-inch tin with melted butter.
Spread half the mixture over the bottom.
Chop the apricots.
Mix with lemon rind.
Spread over the crumb mixture and cover with remaining mixture.
Cook in moderate oven (350°) for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into bars and leave to cool in tin.
Sprinkle sugar over. Delicious when topped with ice cream or cream.

title: paella
directions: Brown chicken pieces in olive oil.
Add chorizo and break apart with a fork.	Add ham and brown slightly. Stir in onion, green pepper, tomato and garlic. Push vegetables and meat aside. Add rice to center of pan and saut 5 minutes.
Then add chicken broth and stir in saffron. Cover. Simmer 25 minutes. Stir in shrimp, pimento and peas. Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.

title: orange salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together Cool Whip, cottage cheese and dry orange Jell-O.
Stir until well blended.
Add 1 can drained mandarin oranges and drained pineapple.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch dish or pan and garnish with second can of drained oranges.
Chill.

title: baked pears
directions: Place pears in baking dish.
Combine all other ingredients in saucepan; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture is clear and thick.
Spread sauce over pears and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: baked tomatoes
directions: Scald tomatoes to remove skins and cut into 1/2-inch slices. Arrange in large, glass baking dish.
Mix next 8 ingredients together and sprinkle over tomatoes.
Top with shredded cheese and butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook until thick. Remove from stove and add 2 tablespoons butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla. Pour into baked pie shell. Add meringue and bake at 425° until meringue is lightly brown.

title: chocolate chip banana nut muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease 12 muffin cups.
In large bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In another bowl, cream the butter and brown sugar for
2 minutes, or until light.
Beat in the eggs.
Stir in the banana, milk and vanilla.
(The mixture will look curdled.)
Add the flour mixture and stir just to combine.
Reserve 2 tablespoons each of the walnuts and chocolate chips and stir in the remaining walnuts and chocolate chips.
Spoon the batter into the prepared muffin cups.
Sprinkle the tops with the reserved walnuts and chocolate chips.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted into the center comes out clean.

title: honey baked apple quarters(appetizer)
directions: Place apples in a shallow-buttered 2-quart casserole.
Combine honey, water, sugar and cinnamon, mixing well.
Pour over apples, turning apples to coat.
Dot with butter.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until apples are tender, basting twice.
Serve with half and half, if desired.
Yields 4 servings.

title: mrs. lula nobles' drop cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cream well.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together and mix well.
Drop by teaspoons on cookie sheets.
Bake at 325°
for 15 minutes.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Combine and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: *May use sugar-free Jell-O and lite Cool Whip.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add boiling water.
Cook until thick. Add flavoring.
Pour into baked crust.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll in chili powder.

title: pumpkin pie bars
directions: Combine flour and sugar; cut in butter.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Beat Eagle Brand, egg and vanilla. Stir in chips and nuts.
Spread over crust.
Bake 25 minutes. Chill thoroughly.
Cut into bars.
Store in refrigerator.

title: fillets and sour cream and cheese
directions: Spread butter or margarine on the bottom of a baking dish. Hold fillets in one layer.
Spread sour cream over fish.
Sprinkle with rest of ingredients.
Bake in 350° oven until fish flakes easily with a fork, 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: beverly's soulful potato salad
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and cook in water until fork goes through potatoes, then drain and rinse.
Boil eggs until hard. Dice onion and eggs.
Combine all other ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add potatoes while they are still warm.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Garnish if desired and place in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook together squash, onion and bell pepper until soft. Drain.
Add pimento, soup, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir and mash together.
Stir stuffing mix into melted margarine.
Place half in the bottom of greased casserole dish.
Place squash mixture on top of crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake at 375° until hot, bubbly and browned, approximately 20 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: frozen punch
directions: Dissolve 4 packages of jello in the boiling water.
Combine sugar with 4 cups of water and bring to a boil.
Add boiling sugar water to dissolved jello.
Set aside to cool.
After thoroughly cooled, add lemon juice and pineapple juice.
Freeze in half gallon milk cartons.

title: grandmother's 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add beaten eggs, one at a time.
Blend each one in thoroughly.
Sift and add dry ingredients alternately with milk and flavoring.
Bake in greased loaf pan in moderate oven (350° to 375°) for 45 to 50 minutes, or bake in two greased layer pans at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Fill and frost as desired.
This recipe is also good for cupcakes.

title: carrot-pineapple muffins
directions: Place doubler paper liners in muffin pan.
In medium mixing bowl, mix the flour, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, baking soda and salt. Mix in eggs and oil.
Beat on medium speed 3 minutes, scraping bowl often.
Stir in remaining ingredients until evenly distributed. Fill each muffin cup half full of batter.
Microcook on High 2 1/2 minutes, rotating after 1 minute.
Test for doneness by inserting wooden toothpick in center of cupcake; they are done when the pick comes out clean (the tops will appear moist).
Carefully remove cupcakes/muffins to rack and remove liners as soon as muffins are removed from pan.
Repeat.
Yields 15.

title: striped delight
directions: Mix crushed cookies and margarine in a medium bowl.
Press firmly into bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate 15 minutes. Beat cream cheese, sugar and 2 tablespoons milk in medium bowl until smooth.
Gently stir in 2 cups of whipped topping; spread over crust.
Pour 3 1/4 cups milk in large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drop 3 cups of Cool Whip by spoonfuls over pudding.
Spread to cover pudding.
Refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: italian fish
directions: Saute all vegetables about 10 minutes over medium heat. Add stewed
tomatoes.
Sprinkle
oregano.
Cook
minutes. Don't stir.
Add fish
(any
kind)
on top of stewed tomatoes. Cover and cook 5 to
10 minutes until fish is white and flaky. Use spatula and flip over onto a plate.
Serves 6.

title: stromboli
directions: Let pizza dough come to room temperature.
Roll out in a rectangular shape, approximately 12 x 20-inch.
Place a row of ham along the 20-inch side, then the Provolone, salami and pepperoni. Shake on the garlic powder to taste and oregano flakes to taste. Roll up starting from the meat side.
Place on a greased pan and put in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until crust browns.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef with garlic salt and onion.
Remove from heat.
Mix soup, sour cream, chilies, one cup cheese and picante sauce into meat mixture.
Fry tortillas in hot oil briefly on both sides in skillet.
Drain excess oil onto paper towels as you remove them from skillet.
Fill each tortilla with meat mixture and place in a shallow baking dish.
Top with remaining meat mixture.
Add water carefully to the sides of the dish.
Top with the remaining two tablespoons of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 12 enchiladas.
This recipe will serve 6 people.

title: old fashioned custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Split chops in half, making a pocket. Cut bread into cubes.
Thinly sliced apple (peel and all).
Heat saute pan.
Add butter, bread and apples; stir.
When the bread is slightly browned, add raisins, cinnamon, nutmeg and sugar.
Toss all ingredients.
Slowly add brandy.
Let reduce.
Spoon mixture into chops.
Bake on rack for one hour.
Yields 2.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: In a mixing bowl, put softened cream cheese, Cheddar cheese, grated onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Mix well and shape into 1 or 2 balls and roll in crushed nuts. Wrap in wax paper and store in refrigerator.

title: corn custard
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
Change water (discard bad beans). Bring to boil and boil 20 minutes.
Do not drain.

title: cheddar burger loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cream cake
directions: Combine dry pudding, sugar and milk.
Beat 1 minute with rotary beater on wire whisk.
Fold in Cool Whip, then pineapple.
Cut cake in layers.
Frost and refrigerate.

title: puppy chow for people
directions: You will need 1 paper bag.

title: smart lady salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water, add sugar and chill.
When slightly thick, beat egg yolks with hand beater until double.
Add egg yolks, vanilla, marshmallows, nuts, pineapple with liquid, cherries, and a pinch of salt.
Pour into a 9 x 13 inch pan and chill for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Fold in cool whip.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in casserole.
Spread on 1 can mushroom soup and 1 cup grated Cheddar cheese.
Set in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: date and walnut bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
In medium saucepan, combine dates and water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally. Cool.
In large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, oats and walnuts.
Stir in butter until mixture is crumbly.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Open the rolls and fill with the chicken.
Mix the soup, milk and cheese and put half in bottom of dish.
Lay rolls on.
Pour rest of the mixture over top of the rolls.
Bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Makes a really good meal by itself.

title: golden coconut cake
directions: Beat first 7 ingredients for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add in flour and baking powder and mix all together. Pour in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven and punch holes with long pronged fork or ice pick.

title: cinnamon french toast
directions: In a shallow bowl, using a wire whisk or fork, beat the egg and egg whites until foamy.
Add the milk, vanilla, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Beat well; set aside.

title: sticky buns(microwave)
directions: Combine, in 8-inch round baking dish, brown sugar, margarine and water.
Cook on 80% (Reheat) for 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir mixture. Cover bottom of pan.

title: breakfast bars
directions: Brown sausage, bell pepper and onion in skillet; drain well. in 9 x 13 inch baking dish, press dinner rolls, leaving no cracks. Spread sausage mixture onto rolls.
Now add cheese onto top of sausage.
Beat eggs and milk well, add salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: nut wafers
directions: Mix ingredients and shape into a long, square loaf. Refrigerate overnight and cut very thin.
Bake on greased cookie sheets at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry congealed salad
directions: Add sugar and water.
Heat and add jello.
Grind cranberries, orange and apples.
After jello is partly congealed, add ground fruit and nuts.
Don't peel fruit but take seeds out.
Use 8-inch square pan for salad.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Melt cheese in microwave or double boiler.
Add crab, scallions and mayonnaise.
Heat until just bubbly.
Serve with corn chips or Melba rounds.
Do not substitute for any of the ingredients!
Not a lo-cal dip, but it will be a hit!

title: stir-fry pepper steaks
directions: Mix soy sauce, sugar, garlic powder and ginger in medium bowl. Add beef; let stand 10 minutes to marinate.

title: strawberry pretzel pie
directions: Melt margarine; mix with pretzels to form crust.
Bake crust at 350° for 10 minutes (cool).
Cream sugar and cheese; add Cool Whip.
Spread mixture into cooled crust.
Mix water and jello until dissolved; add frozen berries to jello.
Pour into crust. Let chill in refrigerator until firm, several hours or overnight.

title: potato casserole
directions: Make a sauce of 1/2 stick margarine with a little flour and 1 pint milk or less.
Season with salt and pepper.
Slice potatoes and eggs.
Put layer of potatoes on bottom of casserole dish. Spread all other ingredients.
Top with a layer of potatoes.
Pour sauce over casserole.
Bake slowly until done.

title: cheesy chicken
directions: Lightly grease a cake pan, 9 x 13 (glass).
Place chicken in pan.
Cover chicken with 8 slices Swiss cheese.
Mix cream of chicken soup with 1/4 cup water.
Put over cheese.
Put seasoned stuffing mix over soup.
Melt butter and shake some garlic powder to taste.
Drizzle over stuffing mix and bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: potato-ham casserole
directions: Layer thinly sliced potatoes, 1/2 of the ham and a few onion flakes, 1/2 oleo, salt and pepper.
Mix each can of soup with 1 can milk; mix well, pouring 1/2 over each layer.

title: italian chicken
directions: Cook chicken (cut in bite size pieces) in dressing.
Add other ingredients and cook until some of the water has cooked out.
Also great with steak or turkey.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Start in 400° oven for 15 minutes. Cut heat to 300°.
Cook for about 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Preheat broiler.
Broil steak until medium rare, about 7 to 8 minutes on each side.
Cool lightly, slice into 1-inch strips.
In a large skillet, saute onion and pepper in the butter or oleo.
Add steak strips, stir in gravy mix, water and soy sauce.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes.

title: red devil balls
directions: Cream softened cheese and
deviled
ham
together.
Add nuts. Chill in refrigerator
until
firm	enough	to
handle. Shape into small balls and roll in finely chopped nuts.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix together and chill.
Add onions, if desired.

title: how to preserve a husband(for wives only)
directions: First, use love/charity, care and get a husband.
Not too young; but tender and healthy.
Make your selection carefully and let it be final.
Otherwise, they will not keep.
Like wine, they improve with age.
Do not pickle or put in hot water.
This makes them sour.
Prepare as follows:

title: swedish pancakes
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Add remaining ingredients, except butter and powdered sugar.
Heat skillet.
Pour in batter to lightly coat bottom.
Tilt skillet, rolling batter around to cover bottom evenly.
You want a very thin layer of batter.
Cook about 1 minute until lightly browned on bottom.
Pour a little melted butter on pancake; sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Loosen with spatula, roll, add a little more butter and powdered sugar and serve.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: ardell's "oatmeal cake"
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, pour boiling water over oats and butter.
Cover; let stand 20 minutes.
Then add white and brown sugar.
Blend in
eggs, flour, salt, cinnamon, baking soda and nutmeg.
Cream well. Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake 35 minutes.

title: molded asparagus salad
directions: Drain asparagus; set aside.
Combine salt, sugar, vinegar, lemon juice and 1 cup water; bring to boil.
Sprinkle gelatine over 1/2 cup water in large bowl.
Pour hot liquid over gelatine and stir until gelatine is dissolved.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Combine onion, celery, water chestnuts, pimento and asparagus last.
Fold into gelatine mixture with few drops green food coloring.
Pour into greased 5-cup mold.
Chill until firm

title: apricot salad
directions: Combine jello and crushed pineapple in a saucepan and heat until jello is dissolved.
Cool.
Combine buttermilk and Cool Whip with jello mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: caponato
directions: Heat olive oil in large frying pan.
Add celery and cook until tender, stirring often.
Remove celery from pan with slotted spoon and set aside.
Add eggplant to pan and saute over medium heat, stirring, until lightly browned and tender enough to mash easily.
Add onion and continue cooking and stirring until onion is soft but not brown.
With slotted spoon, lift eggplant and onion from pan and add to celery.
Pour vinegar, sugar, tomatoes and water into pan.
Simmer over medium heat for 5 minutes stirring.
Return eggplant mixture to pan.
Stir in capers, olives and parsley.
Simmer, uncovered, about 20 minutes.
Add salt if desired.
Remove from heat, cool and refrigerate in covered jar, at least overnight or for a week.
Serve at room temperature, using as an appetizer with toasted baguette slices.

title: party snack mix
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
In a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan or two 13 x 9-inch pans, melt margarine.
Add Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces; mix well.
Stir in cereals, pretzel sticks and peanuts. Sprinkle with salt and garlic powder.
Toss well.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly toasted, stirring occasionally.
Makes 12 cups.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients over low heat.
Place cereal in a large bowl and pour hot mixture over top.
Stir to cover cereal. Pour powdered sugar in a large, clean paper bag.
Then add chocolate covered cereal and shake.
Place candy in airtight container.

title: lemon delight
directions: Cut flour and margarine into coarse meal.
Stir in 1/2 cup nuts and press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool, leaving in pan.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in refrigerator for several hours.
Then serve.

title: cream cheese treats
directions: Cream together.
Roll slices of bread flat with a rolling pin. Spread each slice with cream cheese mixture.
Roll each slice like a jelly roll.
Dip in melted butter, then a cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes with cheese
directions: Combine soup and milk.
In buttered 2-quart casserole, arrange ingredients in layers.
Pour soup and milk mixture over ingredients.
Finish with shredded cheese on top.
Bake in moderate oven until bubbly and done.
Can be refrigerated overnight until ready for baking.

title: potato candy
directions: Cook potatoes and mash.
Add sugar.
Roll out.
Spread peanut butter on top.
Roll up in roll and refrigerate 1 hour or more; slice.

title: chicken patties
directions: Combine seasoning packet for stuffing.
Mix with hot water in bowl.
Stir in eggs, stuffing crumbs, chicken and 1/2 soup.
Form into 6 patties.
Brown well on both sides in butter.
Heat remaining soup and serve on top.

title: four layer delight
directions: Third layer:
Blend well and pour over second layer.

title: linguine salad
directions: Boil linguine according to directions on package; drain and cool.
Mix together remaining ingredients thoroughly, then add linguine.
Refrigerate overnight.
Stir several times.
Will keep well 4 or 5 days.

title: baked cheese cake
directions: For crust, combine crumbs, 1/3 cup butter and 1 tablespoon sugar; press into spring-form pan.

title: quick peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in an 8 x 12-inch dish.
Mix milk, flour and sugar; add to melted margarine.
Add peaches; do not stir.
Bake at 375° for about 40 minutes or until browning is noted.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining items.
Pour in loaf pan.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: strawberry dessert(sugar-free)
directions: Tear cake into small pieces and put into a 13 x 9-inch glass dish. Mix Jell-O and boiling water together. Stir until Jell-O is dissolved. Add 7-Up and stir well. Pour on cake. Put in the refrigerator until set. Layer sliced strawberries on cake, as many as you like. Just before serving, spread with lite or sugar-free Cool Whip.

title: salmon chowder
directions: Cook celery and onion in water and bouillon until tender.
Add potatoes.
Simmer until tender.
Add salmon, corn, soup, milk and margarine.
Serve with soup crackers.

title: nutty o's
directions: In a large saucepan, heat brown sugar, corn syrup and butter until sugar is dissolved.
Stir in cereal and nuts; mix well. Spread onto greased 15 x 11 x 1-inch baking pan.
Cool completely.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 16 cups.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix Russian dressing, soup and jam together.
Put chicken pieces in baking dish and pour mixture over the top.
Bake at 250° for 3 to 3 1/2 hours.
Mixture can be used as a gravy on rice or mashed potatoes.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Line baking pan (13 x 9 x 2) with parchment paper; set aside. Prepare cookie portion of recipe. Cream butter until smooth; add sugars and beat until smooth. Beat in eggs and vanilla. Into a large bowl, sift together flour, salt and baking soda. Slowly beat dry ingredients into wet mixture. Fold in chocolate chips. Take half of cookie mixture and line bottom of baking pan. Do not pack in and leave somewhat uneven. Make sure there is mixture in all corners.

title: tortellini soup
directions: Heat oil in medium heat in soup pot.
Peel and coarsely chop the onion, adding it to the pot as you chop.
Add garlic and cook; stirring occasionally until tender, about 3 minutes.
Add the mushrooms and cook until they begin to release their liquid, about 2 minutes.

title: muriel's chicken casserole
directions: Boil the chicken until done.
Cut up and spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soups with milk and spread over chicken. Spread the stuffing mix on top.
Pour the chicken stock over the stuffing. Dot with the butter and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream pie
directions: Use egg whites for meringue, whipping with 6 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla.
Or, Cool Whip can be used as an alternate topping.

title: bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, mix dry ingredients.
Set aside.
In another large bowl, mix wet ingredients.
Combine wet mix into dry mix, stirring well.
Spray muffin tins with nonstick coating.
Fill 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Refrigerate leftover batter to bake another time.
It will keep for several weeks.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Mix sugar and evaporated milk.
Bring to a boil.
Turn down flame to medium heat.
Add semi-sweet morsels, butter and peanut butter; stir constantly.
Test for consistency by using 1/2 cup cold water or using a candy thermometer (240°).
Remove from heat. Add marshmallows or Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla and mix with whisk or mixer.
Save some Marshmallow Creme to swirl in candy after mixing.
Butter 9 x 12-inch cake pan or larger platter.
Pour candy in pan.
Chill.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cincinnati chili
directions: Place raw ground beef and onion in water; stir until meat separates.
Boil slowly for 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 3 hours.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove fat.
Heat.

title: broken glass dessert
directions: Dissolve each jello in 1 cup hot water;
add 1/2 cup cool water.
Pour each color jello into separate 8 x 8-inch square pan and chill until firm.
Bring to boil the pineapple juice, water and sugar; stir in lemon jello.
Refrigerate to consistency of raw egg whites.
Whip whipping cream and mix into lemon mixture.
Cut the 3 colors of jello into 1/2-inch cubes.
Fold in lemon-cream mixture.
Pour in pan and let stand until firm.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into tube pan; bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool, then glaze.

title: prune cake
directions: Blend sugar and oil.
Add eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Add vanilla, nuts and prunes.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Frost with "Brown Frosting."

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar and cream until light and fluffy. Add eggs, syrup and salt; beat well.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake on lower shelf of oven at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until set.
(I use deep pie shells; this makes two nice pies.
I use Golden Eagle syrup.)

title: easy caramel icing
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add brown sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil.
Add evaporated milk, stir.
Return to a boil.
Remove from burner and add 2 cups 4x sugar, stirring until spreading consistency.
Add more milk or sugar as needed for spreading consistency.
Will frost 3-layer cake.

title: chocolate fudge delight
directions: Mix flour, margarine and nuts; press in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Pat down and bake for 25 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1/2 of Cool Whip.
Spread over baked mixture.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread over cream cheese mix, adding remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts on top. Refrigerate.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Sift together first 4 ingredients.
Cream together sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg. Add milk, oats and raisins.
Mix well.
Add sifted dry ingredients and blend.
Drop by teaspoonful onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 12 minutes.

title: fresh tomato salad
directions: Mix vegetables with the oil, vinegar, salt and pepper.

title: cheese soup
directions: Place water in pan.
Add bouillon and onion.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add vegetables, potatoes and chicken soup.
Cook 20 minutes and add Velveeta until melted. Serve.

title: luncheon snack quickie
directions: Make macaroni as directed on box.
Add the tuna, peas, onion and salt.
Mix all this together and serve alone or with crackers.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine listed ingredients.
Stir by hand until well mixed.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 25-30 minutes and frost (if desired) while warm.
Nuts can be added to this if desired.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed. Drain well.
Mix with softened cream cheese and mushroom soup.
Put in greased casserole and top with onion rings.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: mom's sauce
directions: Heat oil.
Saute onions, garlic and parsley until tender (5 minutes).
Add meat; saute until browned.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, salt, oregano, basil and pepper.
Mix well, mashing tomatoes.
Let simmer for 2 hours or longer, stirring occasionally.

title: dirt pudding
directions: Put most of the crushed Oreos in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Reserve some for top.
Mix cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Mix in the Cool Whip.
Mix in pudding and milk.
Pour mixture over crushed Oreos.
Add reserved Oreos to the top.

title: italian spaghetti sauce
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet.
Add onion, green pepper and garlic and cook until onion is lightly browned.
Add meat and brown.
Then add tomatoes, tomato sauce and seasonings.
Cover and simmer slowly 1 1/2 - 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Mix; chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: french silk chocolate pie
directions: Mix butter and sugar until blended.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla at medium speed.
Beat in eggs to mixture one at a time. Take 5 minutes to add each egg.
Pour into cooked pie shell. Chill pie before you add Cool Whip and garnish with shaved chocolate.

title: magic cookie bar pie
directions: Note:
You can add additional chips and/or nuts, if desired. You can substitute chocolate chips with peanut butter or butterscotch chips; walnuts with peanuts or pecans or create your own mixture.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles per instructions on package.
While noodles cook, cook stew meat until lightly browned.
Add cheese (as much as you like; I use 3/4 package) and cream of mushroom soup.
(I spice up my meat a little with salt, pepper and garlic; use your own preference.)
Simmer meat and cheese 3 to 5 minutes.
When noodles have cooked, stir meat into noodles.
You have a simple but delicious main dish.

title: best blueberry muffins
directions: Cream together butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and vanilla.
Add blueberries. Grease muffin tins.
Pile high.
Sprinkle tops with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: siebert's 7 layer jello
directions: Each jello layer is made with 1 cup boiling water and 1/2 cup cold water.

title: sunshine carrots
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and ginger.
Add orange juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in butter.
Pour over cooked carrots.

title: whipped cream frosting
directions: Mix the flour with 1/2 cup milk until very smooth.
Add 1/2 cup milk; continue stirring.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until very thick.
Cool.
Cream together 1 stick oleo, the Crisco, vanilla and sugar.
Combine both mixtures; mix until smooth.
Tastes smooth like whipped cream.

title: chicken and shrimp soup
directions: Mix cream of celery and cream of chicken soup.
Add water and stir until mixture is smooth.
Add rice and stir well.
Add seasoning and bring to a slow boil.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces.
Add chicken and cook for 45 minutes.
Then add shrimp and cook for another 3 to 4 minutes or until pink.

title: sheila's salsa
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add sour cream, salsa and Cheez Whiz.
Mix well and cook on medium heat until thick.
Great with tortilla chips.

title: corn soup
directions: Cook all ingredients together until the meat is tender.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind first 8 ingredients. Add cloves. Boil 30 minutes. Seal in jars. Makes 8 pints.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Mix and bake for 15 minutes or less at 350°.
The bigger the cookie the better it is.
Makes about 4 dozen large cookies.

title: mrs. perini's special chicken
directions: Grease bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and milk together.
Pour some of the mixture in the bottom of the baking dish.
Layer fresh raw vegetables on the soup mixture.
Place skinned chicken breasts over raw vegetables and pour rest of soup mixture over the chicken and vegetables, covering completely.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese, then sprinkle bread crumbs over the top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for one hour.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: club crackers
directions: Blend together all ingredients.
Spread on crackers.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 7 minutes.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients, cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs. Combine egg and cream add all at once stirring just enough to moisten. Spread dough in greased 8 x 1 1/2 inch round pan, building up edges slightly. Bake at 450° for 15 to 18 minutes. Remove from pan; cool on racks 5 minutes. Split in 2 layers; lift top off carefully. Butter bottom layer. Spoon berries and cream between layers and over top. Serve warm.

title: pudding wiches(kids love these!)
directions: Add the milk gradually to the peanut butter in a deep, narrow bowl, blending until smooth.
Add pudding mix.
Beat slowly with a hand beater or low electric mixer speed.
Let stand for 5 minutes. Spread filling 1/2 inch thick on 12 crackers.
Top with remaining crackers and freeze.

title: candy crunchies
directions: In double boiler or similar pot, slowly melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels.
When mixture is completely melted, add chow mein noodles and nuts.
Fold mixture until noodles and nuts are completely covered with chocolate.
Keep stove on low so as to keep a consistency easy to work with.

title: applesauce jello
directions: Make jello; add 1/4 cup cold water.
Measure 1 cup jello; add applesauce and cinnamon.
Chill 1/2 hour; chill rest of jello until syrupy.
Mix Dream Whip.
Mix 1/4 cup jello and Dream Whip; put on top of applesauce jello.

title: fruitcake bars
directions: Soak the raisins in the bourbon for 1 hour.
Set aside.
Cream the butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and mix together. Add fruits and pecans.
Bake at 350° in jelly roll pan 25 to 30 minutes or until firm.

title: chicken ball
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix cheese, chicken and Worcestershire sauce.
Add garlic powder and chives for taste and color. Roll in walnuts. Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: homemade irish cream liqueur
directions: In blender container combine all the ingredients; blend until smooth.
Serve over ice if desired.
Store tightly covered in refrigerator up to a month.
Stir before serving.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
When ready to serve, crush chips and mix with dressing into bowl of first ingredients.

title: carrot cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Mix flour and other spices and add a little at a time, stirring well. Fold in carrots and nuts.
Bake in layer pans or oblong pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Frost with a cream cheese frosting.

title: pecan butter balls
directions: Cream margarine.
Add flour, salt and sugar.
Blend well.
Add pecans.
Roll into small balls (about 1 inch).
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 325° for about 25 minutes or until light brown.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.
Cool and store in airtight container.

title: apple pie
directions: Peel and core the apples and slice about 1/4-inch thick. Blend the sugar, flour and salt together. Sprinkle 1/4 of the mixture on the bottom crust, then stir the rest through the apples.
Put apples into pie pan compactly, forming a mound in the center. Sprinkle on lemon juice and seasoning and add butter in small pieces.

Put on the top crust and cut vents near the center for steam to escape; trim the edges and seal to the bottom crust. Bake in preheated 425° oven for 40 to 50 minutes until apples are fork-tender and crust is tender and golden brown.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Cut chicken breasts in half, wrap in bacon.
Line bottom of pan with chipped beef, lay chicken on top and pour over it a mixture of soup and sour cream.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake for three hours at 275 degrees, uncovered.
Serve with rice.
The chicken breasts can be cut into quarters for smaller servings.
The sauce can be doubled and the chipped beef can be doubled.

title: sugar 'n cinnamon pecans
directions: Beat whites and add water. Add nuts. Mix and soak for a while. Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon. Add to nuts. Mix well. Bake at 275° for 45 to 50 minutes. Enjoy!

title: holiday potato dish
directions: Remove skins from potatoes; shred into bowl.
Saute onion in 1/4 cup melted butter until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soup and sour cream.
Pour over potatoes and cheese; mix well. Turn into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover; refrigerate overnight.
Sprinkle with corn flakes.
Drizzle with 3 tablespoons of butter.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.
Makes 12 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Pop corn as usual.
Put in large pan in oven at 250° to keep warm.
In heavy pan, melt margarine.
Add sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Cook until temperature reaches 248° on candy thermometer. Add baking soda (this will foam).
Pour over popped corn in a thin stream and stir well.
Put corn back in oven for 45 to 50 minutes. Stir every 15 minutes during that time.
Put on waxed paper to cool.

title: aunt betty's pound cake
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and oil.
Add eggs one at a time. Add flour and milk alternately.
Add flavorings and baking powder.
Bake in greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in preheated oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.

title: no-peek chicken(meal in one dish)
directions: Lightly grease baking dish.
Mix together in a bowl the first 6 ingredients and pour into baking dish.
Arrange chicken on top. Sprinkle with onion mix.
Seal with aluminum foil and bake in 350° oven for 2 hours.
Don't peek!

title: spaghetti con aglioe olio(spaghetti with garlic and olive oil)
directions: Brown the garlic in olive oil until golden brown.
Add salt, pepper and parsley.
Cook spaghetti until done.
Pour 1 cup water from drained spaghetti into oil and garlic mixture.
Mix spaghetti with oil and garlic with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 2 to 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and let drain.
Fry onion in margarine.
When tender, add Cheez Whiz and mushroom soup.
Stir until well mixed. Add rice and broccoli.
Pour mixture into casserole and top with croutons.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: creamy vegetable soup
directions: Melt butter in large pot.
Mix over low heat the flour and butter; add stock.
Cook slowly, stirring constantly, until desired consistency.
Add cooked vegetables which have been slightly mashed, leaving chunks.
Add half and half.
Heat.
Add salt and pepper to taste and a dash of nutmeg.
Serve hot or cold. Serves 4.

title: easy coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake batter as directed on package.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken divine
directions: Mix soup, mayonnaise, sour cream, onion, lemon juice, and cheddar cheese together.
Put layer of chicken in the bottom of greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish, then a layer of chopped broccoli, then layer of soup mixture.
Repeat until all is used.
Sprinkle additional grated cheese on top.
(Crushed cracker crumbs may also be used.)
Bake uncovered 350° oven for 30 minutes or 300° oven for 1 hour.

title: baked grits, cheese and sausage casserole
directions: Fry small pieces of sausage and drain thoroughly.
Stir grits gradually into 6 cups boiling water; cook until thickened.
Beat eggs until thickened; beat in seasonings.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix chili with cream cheese.
Heat on low until cream cheese is melted, stirring regularly.
Add olives and green chilies. Heat until hot.
Serve with Fritos, excellent for parties and kids love it.

title: peachy chicken salad
directions: In a large bowl, stir the mayonnaise, milk, salt, pepper and tarragon until smooth. Add chicken and toss to coat. Stir in the grapes, peas, peaches and pecans. Serve in a lettuce-lined bowl, if desired. Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: broccoli cheese bake
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on the package until tender.
Cook soup, milk and cheese until melted.
Add rice and drained broccoli.
Add chestnuts, if desired.
Place in ovenproof dish and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter ice cream
directions: Add all ingredients together, adding milk to "fill line" and follow freezing directions on your ice cream freezer.

title: microwave cocoa fudge
directions: Microwave sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine on High until margarine is melted, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir until smooth. Blend vanilla and nuts.
Spread into 8-inch square buttered pan. Cool; cut into squares.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In baking pan, mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Cool and ice with favorite icing.

title: linguini con piselli(pasta with peas)
directions: In a large skillet, heat butter and oil together.
Add onion and Prosciutto and cook over medium heat until soft, 5 to 7 minutes.
Add parsley, basil, nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Stir to coat with butter.
Add broth and cook until smooth.
Add cream and continue to cook until slightly thickened.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in pan; simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add butter and vanilla.
Stir until blended.
Serve at room temperature.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix string beans and mushroom soup; mix well.
Place in casserole dish and place onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: homemade sweet tomato sauce
directions: In large kettle, saute onions and garlic until onions are pearly.
Add tomatoes, paste and green pepper.
Simmer a few hours.
When consistency is to your liking, add parsley, salt, pepper and sugar.

title: banana, pineapple, cool whip salad
directions: Make pudding (follow directions on side of package).
Mix all ingredients
together. Refrigerate for 4 hours.

title: oriental barbecued pork skewers
directions: *Ingredients are available in Oriental food section of Jewel or other large food store chains as well as Oriental markets.

title: caribbean fish pot
directions: In a large heavy pot, cook the bacon over medium heat until translucent.
Add the okra and continue cooking until the bacon is slightly brown, about 5 minutes.
Add the oil, bell peppers, onion and garlic; continue cooking until the vegetables are softened, 7 to 10 minutes.
Add the tomatoes, chili, thyme, bay leaves and cayenne pepper, cook over medium-low heat for 15 minutes.
Add the clam juice and chicken broth and cook, partially covered, for 30 minutes more.
Add the fish fillets and scallops, cook, uncovered, over medium-high heat for 2 minutes.
Add the shrimp and cook 2 minutes longer.
Add the crabmeat and cook 1 minute more.
Stir gently after each addition.
Fold in the orange zest and sprinkle with the cilantro.
Serve immediately.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix and bake 2 hours at 300°.

title: honey and lemon chicken
directions: Heat margarine in frying pan and brown chicken on all sides. Transfer to a lidded casserole.
Boil honey, lemon juice and rosemary in the frying pan for a few minutes and then pour over the chicken.
Cover the casserole and cook in a pre-heated oven at 375 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Combine flour, salt and sugar in a mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in oats. Sprinkle water evenly over surface.
Stir with a fork until all ingredients are moistened.
Shape dough into a ball; chill.
Roll to fit a 9-inch pie plate.

title: orange paradise
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender and mix.
Serve with fresh orange slice.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Combine 1/2 stick margarine (melted), soup and sour cream. Mix with potatoes and ham.
Put mixture in greased casserole dish. Mix corn flakes with the rest of margarine (melted) and spread on top of casserole.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 35 minutes, then uncover and bake another 10 to 15 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add celery, pepper, onion and carrots.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix potatoes, onions, salt, pepper and chicken soup.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Cover dish.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.
Last, sprinkle cheese on top.
Return to oven until cheese is melted.

title: poppy seed nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pans).
In a large bowl, beat together sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, evaporated milk, poppy seed filling and nuts.
Pour into two well-greased loaf pans.
Bake for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: mexican chip dip
directions: Put cream cheese down in casserole dish to cover bottom. Spread chili on top of cream cheese.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Garnish with green onions and olives.
Bake in oven for 15 minutes at 350° or microwave about 5 minutes on High.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Place pineapple in greased baking dish.
Mix together 1 cup sugar and flour or cornstarch.
Mix with pineapple.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top of pineapple.
Sprinkle crushed crackers evenly over pineapple and cheese.
Pour melted margarine over all. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pea salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine peas, celery, cauliflower and onions.
Combine dressing and sour cream. Pour over salad; mix well. Cover and refrigerate for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal chip bars
directions: Beat margarine, sugars, eggs and vanilla until fluffy.
Blend in next 5 dry ingredients.
Stir in oatmeal and 3/4 cup chocolate chips.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/4 cup chocolate chips on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cabbage coleslaw
directions: Mix vinegar, oil, salt and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Pour over cabbage.
Toss.

title: millionaires bars
directions: Melt caramels in milk over low heat; stir in pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Chill.
Melt butter and chocolate over low heat or double boiler.
Remove from heat.
Dip caramel into chocolate and return to wax paper.

title: whipping cream pound cake(from the kitchen of carolyn norman)
directions: Mix the ingredients well.
Add 3 cups plain flour and 6 eggs, one at a time, alternating with flour.
Pour into a greased and floured stem pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Test for doneness (inserted toothpick comes out clean).

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: In a large bowl, combine cake ingredients.
Mix until smooth. Pour into
a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: flowerpot cake
directions: You will need 1 new flowerpot (8 x 10-inch), silk flowers and gummy worms.

title: raisin coffee cake
directions: Boil raisins in water until liquid is reduced to 1 cup.
Add butter.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Blend in egg and liquid mixture.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes. Frost while warm with a mixture of cream cheese and powdered sugar.

title: rainbow beauty
directions: Mix and chill gelatin.
Alternate layers of ingredients in footed stemware.
Make the first layer of strawberry gelatin. Fruit cocktail is the second layer.
Cool Whip is the third layer. Add the lemon gelatin, then the fruit and Cool Whip.
Add another layer of red gelatin, then Cool Whip.
Top with nuts, if desired.

title: veggie wedgies
directions: Spread out crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Pinch seams together and bake until golden.
Cool completely.

title: creamy corn
directions: Mix corn, cream cheese, salt, and pepper.
Heat on High in microwave until cream cheese is melted.
Serve hot.

title: easy egg drop soup
directions: Heat the broth until boiling.
Whip the eggs in a separate bowl along with the salt.
Pour the egg mixture slowly into the boiling broth.
The hot broth will cook the eggs into strings. When all of the egg is cooked, the soup is ready to eat.

title: best bran muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine oats, flours, cereal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Make a well in center.
Combine egg, oil, molasses, buttermilk and pineapple.
Pour into well.
Mix only until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in nuts, etc.
Fill 18 greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: old-fashion fudge
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients and cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add butter, vanilla and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour onto platter and let cool.

title: baked pork chops and rice
directions: Flour and brown pork chops.
Cook rice as directed on package. Butter or spray bottom and sides of 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix soup and 1/2 cup water with rice.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: long grain white and brown rice

title: hot pickled beets
directions: Drain liquid from beets into a large pot.
Mix in sugar, vinegar and spices.
Bring to a boil and simmer 10 minutes. Strain liquid and discard spices.
Bring liquid to a boil. Dissolve cornstarch in cold water.
Stir slowly into liquid until slightly thickened.
Add beets and simmer to flavor.
Serve hot as a side dish.

title: french beef slice
directions: Cut bread in half length wise. Remove inside of bread and break into bite size pieces. Brown chuck and onion in skillet, drain. Add 1 Tbsp. vegetable oil. Stir in soups and bread pieces. Spoon mixture in bottom half of bread shell. Cover with top half. Wrap in foil and bake 350 for 30 minutes. Slice across to serve.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except pecans with hand mixer; put one cup chopped pecans in pie shell.
Pour mixture in pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°; lower temperature to 350° and bake another 20 or 30 minutes until pie sets.

title: light and easy chicken divan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake chicken breasts 30 minutes. Steam broccoli
just
until
it
turns
bright
green.
Bring chicken broth to a boil in a saucepan.
Dissolve cornstarch in cold
milk, then
slowly
add
to
chicken broth.
Stir until mixture reaches
a
boil.
Stir
in
yogurt and curry powder. Place broccoli and chicken in baking dish and cover with curry mixture. Top
with grated cheese and bake uncovered for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: roast potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut each red potato into quarters. Place potatoes in large roasting pan with oil and remaining ingredients; toss to coat.
Roast potatoes 20 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: fish casserole
directions: Grease a 2 quart casserole.
Place 4 pieces fish on bottom of casserole.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of the walnuts and raisins, then top with 1/2 of the bread crumbs, cheese and garlic.
Drizzle a small amount of oil over all.
Repeat with remaining ingredients.
Add about a 1/2 cup of water through casserole. Cover and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until fish is heated through and top is brown.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender; drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into greased casserole dish.
Top with buttered crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat & onion; drain.
Mix together all ingredients and simmer for a while.

title: marinated grilled chicken
directions: Mix dressing, soy sauce and pineapple juice.
Use fork to poke holes in chicken breasts.
Pour half marinade over chicken and refrigerate for 1 hour.
Reserve remaining marinade for grilling. Line grill with aluminum foil.
Place chicken on grill and pour marinade onto chicken.
When turning chicken, marinate top side with remaining marinade.

title: easy microwave potatoes
directions: You will need a Ziploc bag.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in large deep pan.
Make batter of milk, sugar and flour.
Pour batter over melted oleo; add peaches and bake in very slow oven of 350° until done.
Cool and serve with ice cream, Cool Whip or plain.

title: ed's oatburgers
directions: Combine all ingredients except oatmeal.
Stir.
Add oatmeal. Make burgers and fry.

title: coffee cake
directions: Bake in 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: dieter's dressing
directions: Combine all the ingredients in jar; chill.
Shake well before using.
Contains 24 calories per 1/2 cup.

title: dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all together; keep refrigerated.
Great with carrots, celery, cucumbers and most other vegetables.

title: easy chili(kids cooking)
directions: Place ground beef and onion in a large heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until ground beef is browned.
Pour off grease. Add beans, tomato soup, water, chili powder, salt and pepper. Cover.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: salmon roll
directions: Drain and flake salmon.
Mix together all ingredients.
Chill until firm.
Shape into log and chill until serving.

title: pretzel dip
directions: Mix mustard and vinegar.
Let stand overnight.
Beat eggs and add sugar; mix well.
Add mustard mixture.
Cook over medium heat until thick.

title: pina colada pound cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch tube pan.
Set aside.
In a large mixer bowl, combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, oil, eggs and 1/3 cup pineapple juice.
Beat with electric mixer on low speed until combined.
Beat on medium for 2 minutes.
Add pineapple and coconut; stir by hand until blended.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, or until cake tests done.
Cool; remove from pan.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain juice from sauerkraut.
Rinse with a little water (not too
much);
drain.
Mix
with other ingredients and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: pasta salad
directions: To cooled noodles and broccoli add shredded cheeses (mixed), cucumber, green pepper, onion, bacon bits or any fresh vegetable you like.
Kidney beans are also great.

title: stuffed turkey loaf
directions: Mix 1 cup stuffing mix with vegetables and water; set aside. Mix 1 cup stuffing mix, eggs, turkey and 1/4 cup barbecue sauce. Place 1/3 meat mixture in loaf pan.
Spread on bottom.
Spoon vegetable mixture on meat in log shape.
Cover with cheese slices. Shape remaining meat mixture over vegetables.
Brush with 1/4 cup barbecue sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: beef and noodles
directions: Cut beef into bite size pieces.
Put into a large pot of water.
Add bouillon cubes, onion and carrot.
Cook in oven at 300° for 3 hours.
Remove from oven and put on top of stove.
Add egg noodles.

title: grilled lime chicken with black bean sauce
directions: Place chicken in shallow dish.
Combine lime juice and next 3 ingredients; divide mixture in half.
Cover and refrigerate half and pour remaining half over chicken, turning to coat.
Cover chicken and refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Combine red pepper and onion in a 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave 1 minute on High and set aside.
Position knife blades in food processor bowl.
Add black beans and remaining ingredients. Process 1 minute or until smooth.
Pour bean mixture into saucepan and cook over medium heat until hot.
Keep warm.
Uncover chicken and drain.
Cook chicken without grill lid over medium hot coals about 5 minutes each side.
Baste with refrigerated marinade. Serve chicken with black bean sauce and red pepper sauce.
Serves 4. Contains 255 calories (24% fat).

title: imperial crab
directions: Stir butter in double boiler until melted.
Add flour and stir until smooth.
In a bowl, mix cream, egg yolk, mustard, paprika, seafood seasoning and Worcestershire sauce.
Add this mixture to flour mixture and heat and stir in double boiler until thickened. Remove from heat.
Season with salt and pepper to taste. Carefully add crab meat to mixture.
Place in greased shells or baking dish and bake 15 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 5 shells.

title: chocolate turtles
directions: Melt caramels with cream over hot water; cool about 10 minutes.
Place pecan halves on wax paper in clusters of 3 (one for the head of the turtle and the other two for legs).
Spoon caramel mixture over the nuts, leaving tips of head and legs showing.
Let stand until set (about 1/2 hour).

title: fred's pizza crust
directions: Combine flour, yeast, salt and sugar; stir.
Add vegetable oil and water.
Mix all ingredients.
Knead for 3 minutes.
Put in a bowl, cover and let rise until double in volume.
Punch down. Divide into 2 equal pieces, shape into balls or leave in one piece for 16-inch pizza.
Let dough rest 4 minutes.
Roll out to 12 to 16-inch circles.

title: gail's french strawberry pudding
directions: Crush wafers into fine crumbs.
Put half the crumbs in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Whip margarine, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese together until light and creamy.
Spread over butter crumb mixture.
Spread strawberries over cream mixture. Mix chopped nuts and remaining wafers.
Sprinkle over strawberries.
Chill overnight.

title: surprise muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease the bottoms of 12 muffin cups with shortening or line with paper baking cups.
Beat egg, milk and oil in medium bowl with fork.
Mix flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder and salt with other ingredients until moistened (batter should be lumpy).
Fill muffin cups 1/2 full.
Drop a teaspoon of jelly into the center of each muffin.
Add batter to fill muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle a little sugar and cinnamon on top when out of oven.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: southern style coffee supreme
directions: Dissolve sugar and coffee granules in boiling water. Chill overnight in glass jar.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and salt.
Blend in beet liquid, vinegar and fat.
Cook over moderate heat, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add beets to sauce.
Let stand 10 minutes, if desired, to blend flavors.
Heat to serving temperature.
Makes 6 servings.

title: susie's ugly but good hot sauce
directions: Remove seeds and membranes from jalapenos, mince.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours. Serve with tortilla chips or sliced raw vegetables.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hello dollies
directions: Melt margarine in a square foil-lined Pyrex dish. Add ingredients in order! Do not stir! Cook at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: pretzel jello
directions: Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 7 minutes.

title: cabbage slaw
directions: Add to cabbage and mix well.
Keeps 2 weeks.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup lukewarm water.
Sift flour, sugar and soda together in a bowl.
Work shortening into this mixture. Add milk and yeast and mix well.
Cover and store in refrigerator and use as needed.
Will last several days, if desired.

title: whiskey sweet 'n' sour meat balls
directions: Combine
soup mix and 1/2 cup water.
Beat in eggs with a fork,
add meat and mix well.
Shape into 40 meat balls and brown about 1/3 at a time.
Drain off excess fat.

title: chocolate 'n oat bar
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass).
In bowl, combine flour, oats, brown sugar and butter; mix well.
Reserve 1/2 cup. Press remaining mixture on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 10 minutes.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crust. Sprinkle with nuts and Nestle Toll House morsels.
Top with remaining oat mixture; press down.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until light browned.
Cool.
Store covered at room temperature. Yields 36 bars.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook lasagne noodles al dente; drain.
Preheat oven to 325°. Use baking dish approximately 2 1/2-inches deep.
Cover bottom with sauce and line the dish with a layer of lasagne.
Dot with spoonfuls of Ricotta, slices of Mozzarella and grated Parmesan cheese.
Cover with sauce.
Repeat with another layer of lasagne, sauce and cheeses, until dish is almost filled.
Bake about 45 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes before serving to allow to settle. Serve with additional sauce.

title: john's specialty 1 pan feast
directions: Clean and cut carrots, peppers and onion.
Dice garlic small. Put roast beef and pork in large pan.
Place onions, peppers, carrots, potatoes and garlic around meat.
Add 2 cups water.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for 2 to 3 hours or until done.
Add water as needed.
Serve with Italian bread, applesauce and tossed salad.

title: fish in tomato sauce
directions: Place fish fillet in heated skillet with oil; add onions. Saut about 2 minutes. Add remaining ingredients; let simmer until done.

title: nana's date bars
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: goof-proof pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt.
Add shortening, egg, vinegar and water. Stir with a fork until just moistened; knead slightly.
Shape into balls.
Do not overknead.
Roll out to desired thickness.
Makes 2 tops and 2 bottoms, if thin.

title: blueberry sauce
directions: If blueberries are frozen, thaw first.
Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook and stir 4 or 5 minutes until thickened.
Makes 2 cups.
Serve over pancakes, waffles, ice cream or pound cake.

title: honey bran bread
directions: Dissolve 1 1/2 cups warm water, 1 tablespoon sugar and yeast in small bowl.
Mix 6 cups water, salt, oil and 1 cup sugar or honey in large 13-quart bowl.
Add yeast, table bran, oats, wheat germ and 5 cups flour.
Let set 15 to 20 minutes.
Add rest of flour until right consistency and let rise.
Shape in loaves and bake at 350° for about 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 8 large loaves.

title: lemon lush
directions: Layer flour, melted oleo and chopped nuts.
Mix and press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° until light brown.
Cool.

title: baked pork chops
directions: Season the pork chops with flour, salt and pepper and brown lightly on both sides. Remove chops to baking dish. Place the sliced onion on top of the chops. Combine the rest and put on top of chops. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: far west lamb steaks
directions: Place steaks in mixture of all other ingredients; let stand for at least 1 hour, turning them occasionally.
Broil for 8 minutes on each side.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix ingredients together as given, adding sugar and flavoring to cream when it is whipped.
Add whipped cream last.
Chill and serve.

title: potato bake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan combine sour cream, soup and onion and spread over potatoes.
Melt oleo and cheese.
Pour over potatoes. Cover with corn flakes.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Note:
To crush crackers, place between sheets of wax paper or place in plastic Ziploc bag.
Crush with rolling pin or pound until crushed.

title: queijadinhas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin cups.
Mix all ingredients and fill muffin cups.
Bake until golden brown.
Cool and serve in individual paper holders if available.
The name means "little cheese treats."

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion; drain.

Add all other ingredients except beans and simmer 10 minutes or until it looks well blended. Drain only the kidney beans; pour all beans in the crock-pot and add the simmered mixture, stirring to blend.
Cook 1 hour on high.

title: chocolate dainties
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add vanilla and water.
Sift flour with cocoa and stir in.
Add nuts and mix well.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for about 20 minutes.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.

title: cheddar chowder
directions: Simmer veggies and seasonings until tender.
Do not drain. Make a white sauce with flour and milk.
Add cheese.
Put with veggies. Add bacon and simmer until hot. Do not boil.

title: cherry sauce
directions: Mix all the ingredients, including cherry liquid in a small saucepan.
Stir continuously.
Allow to boil and stir until thick. Remove from heat and spread over ham or turkey.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook the spaghetti according to package directions; drain. Stir butter or margarine into hot spaghetti; stir in Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form spaghetti mixture into a "crust".
In skillet, cook meat, onion and green pepper until vegetables are tender and the meat is browned.
Drain off excess fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, sugar, oregano and garlic salt; heat thoroughly.

title: chocolate chip outrageous cookies
directions: Heat oven at 325° to 350°.
Beat sugars, butter, peanut butter, vanilla and egg until creamy.
Mix in flour, oats, soda and salt. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by rounded tablespoon, about 2 inches apart, onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool 1 minute before removing from cookie sheet.
Makes about 2 dozen cookies.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Heat Karo, sugar and Jell-O to a boil and remove from heat. Pour over popped popcorn.
Form into balls and let harden on wax paper or foil.
Then wrap individually.

title: friendship cake
directions: In 1/2 gallon jar combine peach brandy, 1 cup of sugar and canned peaches.
Two weeks later, add 1 cup of sugar and canned pineapple.
After two more weeks, add 1 cup of sugar and cherries. After two more weeks, drain the fruit in colander.
Use fruit in cake and save 1 cup of liquid to start your next cake. Invite a friend over for coffee and cake.
Give your friend a cup of liquid and this recipe so she/he can start their friendship cake.

title: pizza appetizer
directions: Use large cookie sheet.
Spread out rolls in 1 big piece and bake 8 to 10 minutes, according to package directions.
Cool.

title: molded cranberry relish
directions: Pour boiling water over gelatin in bowl and stir until dissolved.
Add relish, pineapple (with syrup), apple, celery and nuts.
Stir until relish is thawed.
Pour into 4 cup mold or 6 to 8 individual molds.
Chill overnight or until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir soup, milk, soy sauce, salt and pepper until smooth.
Mix in beans and 1/2 can onion rings.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes or until hot.
Top with remaining onion rings.
Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: egg substitute
directions: This is equal to 1 egg.
Can be used in cookies or cakes and is especially good if you only have to replace part of the eggs needed (you have 2 eggs and need 4, for example).
This will not work in all recipes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Combine and mix together all the ingredients.
Pour into well-greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight. (Good for Christmas Eve.)
Set out casserole at room temperature 1 hour before baking.
(I don't always do this.)
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until firm and brown.

title: sweet and sour pork chops
directions: Dust chops with flour.
Brown chops in drippings.
Drain any excess fat.
Combine and cook vinegar, sugars, soy sauce and salt to a thin syrup.
Add onion, carrots, green pepper and 2 cups water.
Pour sauce over chops.
Cover and cook slowly for 1 hour or until tender.
You can serve chops and sauce over rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: dump cake
directions: Into a greased pan (approximately 9 x 13-inch), pour the pie filling, then the crushed pineapple.
Sprinkle over dry cake mix, then the nuts.
Pour over melted butter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Spoon out and serve with a topping of ice cream.

title: easy devil's food cake
directions: I cut this to 1/8 and drizzle on top of Bundt.
Very moist.

title: blue ribbon vegetables
directions: In small bowl, combine mayonnaise, milk, mustard and pepper; set aside.
Cook vegetables according to package directions; drain.
Spoon sauce over hot vegetables.
Sprinkle with Parmesan.

title: cheese pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together (will be watery).
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven; leave pies in oven for 1 hour.
Take out and cool.
Top with strained cherry or blueberry pie filling.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients.
Pour over rest and toss well. Refrigerate overnight.

title: no-bake cookies
directions: In a saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa, milk, butter and salt. Bring to a hard boil for 1 minute. Then add oats and vanilla. Mix well and work fast because it wills set up quick. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper. Let cool at least 30 minutes. Makes about 2 dozen.

title: fruit compote
directions: Combine all fruit.
Stir into pudding mix.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: sandwich bread
directions: Set aside 1 cup flour.
Mix remaining flour, sugar, salt and yeast.
Stir in hot water and margarine.
Mix in enough reserved flour to make a soft dough.
On a floured surface, knead 4 minutes.
On a greased baking sheet, roll dough out to 14 inches x 10 inches.
In the center 1/3 length, put beef and cheese in layers.
Cut 1-inch wide strips along sides of filling, out to dough edges.
Fold strips in at an angle across the filling, alternating sides to make a braided effect.
Cover dough.
Place pan over sink full of hot water; let rise 15 minutes.
Brush with beaten egg; sprinkle with caraway seed.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes, or until light brown.
Cool slightly on pan, then serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers; reheat to serve.

title: paella salad(cold)
directions: Cook shrimp in 1 1/2 cups water for 3 to 5 minutes.
Chill and devein.
Cook rice, omitting butter.

title: chop suey
directions: In large pan, place meat and brown.
Then add 1/2 cup soy sauce, browning a bit longer.
When browned, add onions and celery. Put 2 cups water and cook slow for at least 1 hour.
Add water as it cooks out vegetables, both drained.
Mix cornstarch in 1/2 cup water, then stir in meat.
Cook until thick.

title: sponge cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add water; continue beating until very thick.
Gradually beat in sugar, then vanilla.
Sift flour 3 times; fold in egg mixture, a little at a time.
In another bowl, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar; beat until they form moist, glossy peaks.
Fold into first mixture, turning bowl gradually. Bake in ungreased tube pan at 325° for about 1 hour.

title: slaw dressing
directions: Beat eggs and stir in rest of ingredients except butter.
Cook in double boiler until thickened, stirring constantly and adding butter just before removing from heat.
Pour over slaw while hot.

title: microwave spanish rice
directions: In 2-quart microproof casserole, combine all ingredients except rice.
Cook, covered, on High (maximum power) for 5 minutes or until boiling; stir in rice.
Cook, covered, on 50 (Simmer) for 30 to 35 minutes or until rice is tender.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes before serving.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Saute onion, celery, carrots and mushrooms in margarine.
Add chopped cabbage.
Stir and continue to saute.
Add tomatoes and club soda.
Simmer until hot.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Serve immediately.
Can also be refrigerated for 10 days or 2 weeks.
Serves 8.

title: breakfast parfait
directions: Layer alternately in a tall glass and add a strawberry or cherry for garnish.

title: total conversion cake
directions: Bring to boil oleo, water and cocoa.
Mix in large bowl flour, sugar and salt.
Pour oleo, water and cocoa mixture with flour, sugar and salt.
Add eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.
Bake in 350° oven in greased, oblong pan.
The last 5 minutes while cake is cooking, begin icing.

title: nacho's
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan, heat soup and salsa until hot, stirring often.
Serve over tortilla chips and top with chopped tomatoes, green onions, sweet red and green bell peppers and sliced olives.

title: apple salad
directions: Combine salad ingredients and set aside.

title: popovers
directions: Before starting, put greased popover pans into a very hot oven at 450°.
Heat until sizzling.
