Beat eggs at medium speed until frothy.
Add salt, sugar, flour and 1/2 of the milk.
Mix at medium speed until smooth.
Add remaining milk and melted shortening and beat at low speed until blended.
Pour into hot pans and fill each 1/2 full.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 400° and continue baking for another 15 minutes.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Cut biscuits in quarters.
Put all ingredients in medium plastic bag.
Shake up.
Put in pan.
Pour 1 stick melted butter overall.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Let set 10 minutes before dumping out.
Decorate with a few cherries on top.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak 1/2 cup poppy seed for 1 hour in 1 cup water.
Bake cake in layers as directed, except use poppy seed-water mixture in place of water.
Prepare 1/2 recipe Custard Sauce or 1/2 prepared vanilla pudding mix.
Spread between cooled layers.
Frost top and sides with White Mountain Frosting.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes; drain.
Fold in soup, mayonnaise, grated cheese and egg.
Pour in casserole dish and sprinkle crumbled Ritz crackers on top.
Cook in preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: smothered potato
directions: Wrap potatoes in foil without oil.
Bake potatoes in oven for 2 to 3 hours at 350° or until done.
Chop chicken into 1/2 inch cubes, more or less.
Stir-fry chicken in nonstick pan with sprinkling of salt.
Do not use any oil or nonstick spray.
(It will work, I promise you.)
Dilute soup with 1/2 can water and heat as usual.
When potatoes are done take them out and roll until soften, before unwrapping.
Then remove foil and break potatoes open, scatter chicken on potatoes and cover with soup.

title: hearty clam chowder
directions: Saute bacon until crisp in large kettle.
Remove and chop. Add onions, potatoes, green pepper, celery and garlic.
Add 2 cups chicken broth and seasonings.
Cover kettle and simmer 20 minutes. Add clams and juice and half and half; heat until hot.
Do not boil.
Add chopped bacon.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hawaiian ham sandwiches
directions: Preheat broiler.
Open the bulky roll.
On one-half place sliced ham.
On the other half, place a slice of pineapple and put a slice of Swiss cheese on top of that.
Put under broiler until cheese melts.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Mix cornflake crumbs and margarine; put half mixture in the bottom of a casserole dish.
Add raw cabbage.
Mix other ingredients; pour on top of cabbage.
Sprinkle rest of cornflakes on top.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.

title: angel roll sheet cake
directions: Grease 1 large cookie sheet with sides and line with wax paper.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Spread mixture evenly on cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and cool.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes lengthwise; place over bottom of Pyrex dish.
Place pork chops over potatoes.
Cover with can of soup. Place foil over dish and seal.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve with salad or green beans, and you have a balanced meal.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream Crisco, sugars, egg and vanilla together in large bowl.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Blend in sugar mixture.
Blend in water.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by level tablespoonful 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: angel food cake dessert
directions: Beat milk and juices until thickened.
Add pineapple. Alternate cake and filling.
Chill overnight in 8-inch square Pyrex dish.

title: oreo pie(serves 12)
directions: Break cookies in pieces; add softened ice cream and Cool Whip and mix.
Place in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan and freeze.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: hot pepper wieners
directions: Chop wieners to bite size pieces.
Mix vinegar, oil, sugar, salt, wieners and catsup in large pot.
Cook 5 minutes.
Then add peppers.
Cook until peppers are slightly wilted.
Pack in jars. Hot bath for 5 minutes.
Cool and store.

title: yogurt popsicles
directions: Pour into paper cups and put tongue depressor in center. Freeze.

title: chinese cabbage chicken salad
directions: Cut the chicken into chunks and brown.
Crush the noodles and brown them in butter until they are toasted.
Sprinkle Ramen seasoning that comes with the noodles onto the noodles.
Shred the cabbages.
Thinly dice the onions and celery.
Toss all the ingredients together.
Just at time to serve, pour the dressing over.

title: savory veal pot roast
directions: Roll veal in 3 tablespoons flour mixed with paprika; brown meat in fat in Dutch oven and add rest of ingredients, except reserve 1/4 cup water and rest of flour.
Cover and cook over low heat for 2 hours and 30 minutes or until done.
Stir sauce and turn meat during cooking to take seasoning.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: easy chicken stew
directions: Combine first six ingredients in large pot.
Cook until chicken falls off the bone.
Remove chicken from liquid; allow to cool. Remove the meat from the bone and put back into soup mixture.
Add cream of chicken soup and cornstarch, mixed with a little water to thicken.
Add green beans, corn and potatoes to chicken mixture. Serve hot with French bread.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Melt over hot not boiling water, 1 cup peanut butter morsels. Stir until smooth.
In large bowl, combine melted morsels, cream cheese, vanilla extract and salt; beat well.
Beat in powdered sugar alternately with milk until mixture is of spreading consistency.

title: easy chicken in a pot
directions: Note:
When using noodles, remove cooked chicken from pot. Skim off fat.
Pour sauce over noodles.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat small pan; add 1 tablespoon oil and dry scramble the eggs.
Remove and set aside.
Heat wok; add 3 tablespoons oil and 1/2 teaspoon salt.
Add scallions; mix few times.
Add rice and mix in thoroughly.
Add sugar; mix.
Add soy; mix.
Add eggs, cut into small strips or pieces.
Add peas.
Heat through.

title: best waldorf salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and stir well.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: picnic baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients; stir well.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased shallow 2-quart baking dish.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Rinse sauerkraut with cold water.
Mix in large mixing bowl, sauerkraut, celery, green pepper and onion; set aside.
Mix in small bowl, vinegar, salad oil and sugar, mixing until sugar is very well mixed.
Stir this salad dressing into your sauerkraut mix; cover and let set for 1 hour before serving.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Allow hash browns to thaw or defrost in microwave.
Mix all ingredients in bowl until fully mixed.
(Leave some cheese to sprinkle over top.)
Mix hash browns in and pour into casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: osso bucco in clay pot
directions: Chop vegetables and place in bottom of pot.
Dredge veal in flour, seasoned with salt, pepper and oregano.
Place veal on top of vegetables.
Mix and bring to a boil with remaining ingredients.
Pour around veal.
Cover and place in a cold oven set at 450°.
Cook 1 1/2 hours and serve topped with Gremolata. You can also serve with risotto alla milanese or buttered spinach noodles with Parmesan cheese.

title: ham casserole
directions: Cook and drain macaroni. In large mixing bowl, add all the above ingredients and mix lightly. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and dot with butter. Sprinkle with bread or cracker crumbs before baking. Cover with foil and put in preheated 350° oven and bake for 45 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and Crisco.
Cream well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Sift together flour, salt and baking powder. Add milk and flour alternately.
Add flavoring and coconut.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.

title: swiss chocolate cake
directions: Mix and put in 3 cake pans. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli-chicken roll-ups
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
Mix together broccoli, chicken, 1/2 can of mushroom soup and 1 cup cheese.
Spoon this mixture onto tortillas.
Roll up tortillas and place side by side in pan.
Mix remaining soup with milk and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle on remaining cheese and bake 10 more minutes.

title: holiday cut-out cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream first 6 ingredients, then add baking powder and flour and mix well.
Roll out on floured surface 1/8-inch thick and cut into desired shapes.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet for 9 to 10 minutes.
You can sprinkle them with sugar before baking or decorate baked cookies with powdered sugar icing.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except chili sauce and grape jelly together and form small balls.
Brown in frypan.
Remove and pour out all fat.
Put chili sauce and jelly in frypan; heat over low flame until thoroughly dissolved.
Put meat balls back in pan. Add a little water and simmer for 30 minutes.
Stir gently so they don't stick.
You can also let them simmer in a crock-pot on low.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Heat oil in deep heavy pot; add celery and onions.
Stir-fry over moderate heat until onions are transparent but not brown.
Add chicken broth; cover and cook 4 to 5 minutes.

title: oatmeal cake(delicious)
directions: Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Mix well. Let stand until cool.
Cream the butter and sugars. Add vanilla and eggs, one at a time, stirring well after each addition.
Add salt, soda, cinnamon and flour gradually. Add oatmeal.
Pour into large 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: turtle cake
directions: In double boiler melt caramels, butter and milk until smooth. In mixing bowl prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour half of the cake batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch sheet cake pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: oatmeal chocolate cookies
directions: Into a saucepan, put the margarine, sugar, cocoa and milk. Boil and stir, cooking for 3 minutes after the boiling stage. Remove from heat and add the peanut butter, oatmeal and finely chopped nuts (if desired).
Stir vigorously until dough is stiff. While it is still hot, drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: gooey butter coffee cake
directions: Combine cake mix, margarine and 1 egg.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat sugar, cream cheese and 2 eggs until smooth. Pour on top of crust layer.
Bake at 350° (325° if using glass pan) for 30 minutes.
When cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: cajun christmas mix
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
In a large, shallow roasting pan, combine almonds, cereal and goldfish crackers.
Melt margarine and stir in seasonings.
Pour over almond mixture and toss to coat. Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Spread on paper towel to cool.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 9 cups.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli according to package directions; drain. Spread in bottom of casserole dish.
(Do not add salt.)
Mix cream of mushroom soup, cheese, salad dressing, milk and egg; pour over broccoli.
Spread buttered bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: ranch style baked beans
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Drain off grease.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Put in baking dish.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Bake pie crust for 5 to 10 minutes.
Take out of oven; pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut macaroon pie
directions: Beat sugar, eggs and salt real good.
Add butter and flour; blend well.
Add milk and 1 cup coconut.
Pour into pie shell and top with remaining coconut.
Bake at 325° until done.

title: easy cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Can drop spoonfuls on can.
Roll out and cut either one.
Bake at 300° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry banana snootie
directions: Blend all together in blender until smooth. Makes 2 servings.

title: pretzel-strawberry jello salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels, margarine and sugar together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Press into bottom and bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Beat cream cheese with 1 cup sugar.
Stir into the Cool Whip and spread on cooled pretzel crust.
Mix strawberry gelatin, boiling water and strawberries.
Let set in refrigerator until it begins to jell.
Pour over cheese mixture and refrigerate several hours.
This can be served as a salad or dessert.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute broccoli in oleo with mushrooms until broccoli is thawed.
In casserole dish, combine rice, soup, salt and pepper. Add sauteed broccoli and mix in grated cheese.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
May be kept refrigerated overnight before baking.

title: brown stew
directions: Brown meat (after coating with flour in bag) in oil.
Add all ingredients, except vegetables and Bisquick.
Cook 1 1/2 hours. Add vegetables and cook until potatoes are tender.
Follow instructions on Bisquick box for dumplings and add to stew.

title: cavatini
directions: Boil pasta together in salted water until done, drain.
Brown meat and drain, add sauce, onions, pepper, mushrooms, pepperoni and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Spray 9 x 13 casserole with non stick coating.
Pour in pasta and meat mixture, mix and spread cheese over top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake.
Crumble 1/2 cake in bottom of bowl.
Pour 1/2 vanilla pudding over cake, then mix strawberries with glaze and put 1/2 of it over pudding.
Add 1 container of Cool Whip, then repeat.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: game hens a l'orange
directions: Place game hens, breast side up, on a rack in roasting pan and roast in 350° oven for 1 hour or until done.
Keep warm.
In a small saucepan, combine juice concentrate, chicken stock and cornstarch mixture.
Cook over medium heat, whisking constantly until thickened.
Add tarragon, 1 1/2 tablespoons butter sprinkles and pecans.
Heat thoroughly.
Split cooked hens in half.
Spoon some of orange sauce over each half and sprinkle sauce with remaining butter sprinkles.

title: fried rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in large skillet; drain, reserving 2 tablespoons fat.
Cool and crumble bacon.
Get skillet hot; pour in beaten eggs and stir in rice, onions, meat and vegetables. Cook until eggs are cooked, then cover and steam until vegetables are tender.
Stir in bacon; add soy sauce until dark.
Cook 5 more minutes and serve.
We like it served on a bed of fresh lettuce.

title: cream cheese and pecan frosting
directions: Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese, margarine, salt and milk until smooth and creamy.
Stir in nuts.

title: west texas casserole
directions: Cook at 350° to 400° until done.
Grate cheese on top and add olives.

title: jan's fried squash blossoms
directions: Wash and remove all green parts from the blossoms.
Dip in beaten eggs.
Then lay in flour to coat, pressing down on the blossom so it soaks up flour.
Heat oil to medium.
Fry until golden brown on each side.
Drain on paper towels.
Salt and pepper to taste as you are frying.

title: pumpkin bread with cream cheese filling
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients.
Make a hole in center of dry ingredients and add oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Mix very well.
Grease 2 loaf pans, fill each 1/4 full.
Make a "trench" in the middle of the loaf.
Fill with filling (don't let filling touch side of pan). Add batter to sides and then cover filling completely with bread mixture.
Each pan should be 1/2 to 2/3 full when complete.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
(You'll have to hide some for yourself!)

title: bisquick mix
directions: Mix together. Store in airtight plastic canister.
(May wish to refrigerate unless stored in cool place.)

title: mexican layer dip
directions: Layer 1:
Refried beans and taco seasoning.

title: mushroom bread
directions: Separate dough into triangles.
Place on ungreased 12-inch pizza pan; press out dough to fit pan.
Toss mushrooms with margarine; arrange on dough.
Sprinkle with cheese and marjoram. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lebanese meatballs
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon butter until transparent.
Cool slightly.
Mix with meat, egg, bread and seasonings.
Shape into 1 1/4-inch balls; roll them in dry bread crumbs.
Brown slowly in remaining 2 tablespoons butter; drain off all but 2 tablespoons fat.
Gently spoon yogurt over meatballs.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Serve hot over noodles or rice.

title: macaroni luncheon casserole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and place in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Mix soup, milk and salt and pour over mixture. Sprinkle with crumbs and dot with butter. Bake until bubbly and browned. Serves 6 to 8.

title: donna's soup
directions: Saute onion.
Add flour and salt.
Cook until bubbly.
Add bouillon cube, lemon juice and water.
Heat until it boils.
Add and cook corn.
Add and just boil evaporated milk and tomatoes. Add and melt cheeses.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until browned, drain and put in the bottom of an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Pour pizza sauce over beef, then top with cheese.

title: granma's banana bread
directions: In a small bowl, mash bananas.
In a large bowl, cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add flour and soda.
Stir in bananas, nuts and cherries.
Bake 45 minutes to an hour at 350°.
Makes 1 large loaf.

title: best cupcakes
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in heavy pan over low heat.
Add pecans; stir to coat well.
Do not beat.
Remove from heat to cool.
Mix other ingredients.
Stir together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Use paper cup liners.
Makes sixteen cupcakes.

title: aunt ella's macaroni and cheese
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Lightly grease a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.

title: shrimp and crab gumbo
directions: Make a dark brown roux with oil and flour; add bell pepper, onion and celery and cook until onions are transparent.
Gradually add the water and continue cooking for at least 1 hour.
Adjust seasoning to taste; add shrimp, crab, parsley and green onion tops and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice in soup bowls. Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the sugar and eggs together.
Add the oil.
Mix together the flour, salt and soda.
Add to the sugar mixture.
Add the vanilla and cinnamon.
Mix together.
Add the apples and the nuts. Bake in a greased tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes to an hour.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Melt 1 stick of margarine.
Mix with 1 stack of crushed Ritz crackers.
Use for topping on casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy cottage cheese salad
directions: If you use a lot of fruit, etc., use 6 ounce box of Jell-O.

title: zucchini patties
directions: Mix ingredients together and make into patties.
Fry until golden brown.

title: turkey wild rice casserole
directions: Place turkey, mushrooms, carrot, broccoli and broth in saucepan. Cover.
Heat over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Spoon into a 2-quart casserole and keep hot.

title: cheese ball
directions: Remove cheese.
Allow to soften.
Mix all ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap and decorate.
Remove from refrigerator 30 minutes before serving for better flavor.
Serve with crackers or celery.

title: strawberry salad and sweet vinaigrette dressing
directions: Prepare the dressing at least 2 hours before serving.
Mix the sugar, mustard, celery seed, paprika and vinegar and stir every 30 minutes until the mixture has the consistency of honey.
Add the salad oil, slowly with the aid of a whisk or electric mixer (or add syrupy vinegar and oil to an electric blender) and mix until uniform.

title: steak sandwiches
directions: Cut steak across grain about 1/4-inch thick.
Marinate in the dressing (just enough to partly cover the meat, for at least 30 minutes).
Heat medium sized skillet until hot.
Put about 8 ounces of steak pieces into skillet and stir-fry until done.
Do this until all the steak is cooked.
Serve on Hoagie buns with the cheese, lettuce, onion, tomato, etc. according to each person's taste.

title: old-fashion potato soup
directions: Cook, cube
and
drain	potatoes; add milk.
Heat thoroughly and season	with
salt, pepper and butter.	Mix butter, flour, egg and
milk.	Drop
by teaspoon into hot soup.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.

title: milk gravy
directions: Brown flour in grease and add milk, salt and pepper.
Cook on high heat until starts to thicken.
Lower heat and stir constantly until thickened.

title: chili mac*(low-fat, cholesterol and calories)
directions: Cook macaroni per directions on package without salt.
Drain and set aside.
Spray iron pot on skillet with nonstick cooking spray.
Heat until hot.
Add meat, onion, green pepper and garlic. Cook on medium heat about 15 minutes, until vegetables are tender, stirring constantly.
Stir in tomato juice and next 3 ingredients.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add beans and macaroni and simmer an additional 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: best ever corn casserole
directions: Mix oil, sour cream and muffin mix; add corn and cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes. Add 1 cup grated cheese on top; bake until cheese is melted.

title: mounds
directions: Mix together and chill.
Form into balls or Mounds.
Dip in dipping chocolate.

title: chili
directions: Cook hamburger until done; drain.
Add onions, chili powder, salt, tomato juice, water and kidney beans.
Simmer until done. Can use 2 pounds hamburger.
Makes smaller amount.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt the butter in pan. Add the sugar; stir well. Add the egg, pecans, raisins, coconut, vinegar and pumpkin pie spice. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: upside-down cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cook sausage, onions and peppers in skillet until sausage is brown and crumbly. Stir in flour.
Mix in next 4 ingredients.
Remove from heat. Stir in cheese and olives. Spread in a 9-inch square pan.
Prepare muffin mix according to package. Spread over sausage. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Loosen edges.
Invert onto plate. Serve immediately.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Sift flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Beat eggs.
Cream butter and sugar.
Roll into balls size of walnuts, then roll balls in mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Place 2-inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: cookie and cream pie
directions: Put ice cream in a large bowl and let soften for 15 to 30 minutes.
Put Oreos in a large Ziploc freezer bag and crush cookies with a hammer or metal spoon.
Mix cookies with ice cream in the large bowl, using a strong spoon.
Pour mixture into pie crust and freeze for at least 2 hours before serving.

title: caramel bars
directions: Melt the caramels with 1/3 cup of evaporated milk.
Mix the cake mix, melted oleo and 1/3 cup evaporated milk; put half of this mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat in crust and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle 1 cup of chocolate chips over crust, then pour caramel mixture over.
Put rest of cake mix mixture over caramels and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sugar-free ice cream
directions: Variations:
Chocolate chip:
Chop 1 1/2 cup milk chocolate chips in food processor.
Add to mix.
Also 1/2 package sugar-free instant chocolate pudding can replace the vanilla for a better flavor.

title: spoon bread
directions: Combine cornmeal, tapioca, milk, fat and salt.
Cook over boiling water, stirring frequently, until thickened.
Remove from heat; cool slightly.
Beat egg yolks slightly; beat into the mixture.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve from the baking dish.

title: onion-cheese puffs
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and butter to rolling boil. Stir in flour, salt and garlic powder.
Stir vigorously over low heat 1 minute or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat. Beat in eggs until smooth.
Stir in cheese and onion.
Drop dough by teaspoonful 1 inch apart onto lightly greased baking sheet. Bake until puffed and golden, 20 to 25 minutes.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar until fluffy.
Add egg and sour cream.
Combine
flour, baking powder, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Add to batter
and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured 9x13 pan. Combine brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter. Cover and chill overnight.
Bake 350° for 35-40 mins. or until done.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet and drain.
Mix all ingredients in bean pot or casserole dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham rolls
directions: Cut rolls in half horizontally.
Spread butter mixture over both halves.
Cover with a layer of Swiss cheese and shaved ham. Cover with foil.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cut with a sharp knife.

title: pat-in-pan crust
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add oil and mix well.
Pat in 9-inch pie pan, fluting edge, if desired.
Fill with filling.
For baked pie shell, bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: marinated peas
directions: Mix last three ingredients together.
Add first four ingredients to bowl.
Marinate overnight; serve cold.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray pans with Pam (you'll need 3 round pans).
Mix together all ingredients with an electric mixer. Divide batter among the 3 pans.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick.
Cool layers on a wire rack (still in pans) for 10 minutes.
Carefully remove pans and let completely cool.

title: hash
directions: Cook meat until tender and can pull apart. Remove meat from broth and cool. Tear apart. Put potatoes and onions in broth and cook until very tender. Put meat in with other ingredients; let simmer for about 1 hour.

title: famous fryemont cheese soup
directions: Cook vegetables in butter in large pan over medium heat 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in flour. Cook, stirring 3 to 4 minutes over low heat.
Slowly add chicken broth, stirring with Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Simmer covered over very low heat 20 minutes, stirring frequently until vegetables are tender.
Add milk, cheese and salt to taste.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes or until piping hot.
Garnish with almonds.
Serves 6.
(From America's Country Inn Cookbook.)

title: piccalilli
directions: Mix chopped tomatoes with salt and let stand 3 to 4 hours. Squeeze out and discard water.
Combine with other vegetables. Add mustard seed, vinegar and sugar.
Heat just to boiling, then pack into hot jars and seal.
Makes 3 1/2 to 4 quarts.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring dry Jell-O and pineapple with juice to a boil.
Cool, then add buttermilk, nuts and Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil until thick (however thick you want it).
Pour into pie crusts.
Beat egg whites until meringue.
Put on top of pies.
Sprinkle coconut over top and bake in oven until brown.

title: sharon's no bake cookies
directions: Boil butter, milk, cocoa and sugar for 1 minute (after all ingredients are melted).
As soon as you take off the stove, add peanut butter and vanilla.
Stir in flour.
Mix all up.
Then add oats and stir up.
If they're a little dry, add some milk.
Drop by spoonfuls on wax paper or foil.

title: honey butter
directions: Cream butter or oleo.
Beat in honey.
Beat until fluffy. Delicious on hot biscuits or toast.

title: meat loaf
directions: Add salt to flour.
Mix all ingredients well with meat.
Cook in double frypan or roll in foil and bake 50 minutes, or until done, in 300° oven.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Let set out all day covered with a paper towel.
If you are not making bread, discard 1 cup starter or give it to a friend and return remainder of starter to refrigerator.

title: spiced nuts
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg white until frothy. Add water. Beat until soft peaks form. Stir in nuts; toss to coat. Combine sugar and spice. Stir into nut mixture. Spread nuts evenly onto a greased baking sheet. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally; cool on waxed paper. Makes 6 cups.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Put cut potatoes in boiler.
Add all other ingredients.
Add, if necessary, enough water to cover potatoes.
Slow cook until done.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift dry ingredients. Drop in egg with corn. Stir until thoroughly mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls into 370° fat.
Fry until golden brown.
Drain.

title: corn bread stuffing
directions: Prepare corn bread per package; cool and cube.
Boil giblets, celery, 1 chopped onion, butter, salt and pepper in water until giblets are cooked through and veggies are tender. Pull out giblets and dice up.
Mix corn bread, stuffing, eggs, fresh onion, poultry seasoning, giblets and veggies from broth, pouring broth over to moisten but not saturate mixture.
Don't work a lot, just to mix.
Stuff into turkey or heat in oven separate pan until heated completely through.
Heating it outside the turkey makes it crispy on top.
(My favorite way to cook the extra.)

title: chocolate orange cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 9-inch square baking pan.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda, baking powder and salt.
Beat butter, sugar and zest until fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Stir in half the flour mixture, then sour cream, then remaining flour.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake until a toothpick stuck in center comes out clean, 60 to 70 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove to rack and cool completely.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 9 slices.

title: blender coconut pie
directions: In blender container combine milk, eggs, margarine, flour, sugar, vanilla, nutmeg and coconut.
Blend 1 minute.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until custard is set.

title: chocolate cherry upside-down cake
directions: Spread cherry pie filling over bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a large bowl, stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
In another bowl, combine water, oil, vinegar and vanilla. Add liquid ingredients to flour mixture all at once.
Stir just to moisten.
Pour batter evenly over cherry pie filling.
Bake in 350° oven 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool 10 minutes in pan; invert and cool.
Top with Cool Whip if desired.

title: crunchy fudge sandwiches
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter in pan over low heat, stirring until mixed.
Remove from heat.
Add Rice Krispies and mix.
Press 1/2 of cereal mixture into buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill.
Combine chocolate chips, sugar, butter and water over low heat until mixture is blended.
Spread over chilled cereal mixture.
Add remaining cereal mixture.
Chill.

title: irma's easy pie crust dough
directions: *I like to replace about 1/4 to 1/2 tablespoon water with vinegar.
It is supposed to make a more flaky crust.

title: cheese straws
directions: Grate cheese and mix all ingredients together.
Run through cookie press onto a cookie sheet.
Cook in a very slow oven about 250° for 1 hour or until very crisp.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking soda together.
Beat butter with a wooden spoon until light.
Gradually blend in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until fluffy after each addition.
Add sifted flour mixture alternately with mixture of mashed banana and soured milk, beating well after each addition.
Fold in chopped walnuts. Pour into a greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 350° for 65 or 75 minutes or until done.
Turn out of pan onto rack; cool several hours before serving.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix well.
Can be made a day before serving.

title: sausage-bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans as directed on package; drain.
Turn into ungreased 4 1/2-quart casserole.
Add baked beans and kidney beans.
In covered skillet, simmer sausage in small amount of water for 5 minutes.
Drain liquid from skillet.
Panfry sausage until brown on all sides.
Cut each sausage into 2 or 3 pieces. Add with ham to beans.
Stir together remaining ingredients and pour over casserole.
Gently mix all ingredients.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour.
Heat oven to 400°.

title: zesty barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well.
Use on your favorite meats (chicken, turkey, etc.). Refrigerate unused portion.
Will keep well.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large saucepan, cook onions and garlic in butter until golden brown.
Add water, sherry and bouillon.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 30 minutes to blend flavors.
Place soup in 6 ovenproof soup bowls.
Top each with bread slices and cheese.
Broil until cheese melts.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix ingredients as listed and beat by hand until lemon in color and fluffy.
Pour into an unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes or until firm.
(It should have the texture of baked custard.)

title: spaghetti salad(yields 6 servings)
directions: Cook pasta as directed on box.
Finely chop cucumbers (remove seeds), tomato and green pepper.
Toss into cooked pasta.
Pour dressing over mixture.
Mix well and chill.
Enjoy!

title: jalapeno jelly
directions: Put green and jalapeno peppers with 1/2 cup of vinegar in blender and blend.
Pour into 4-quart saucepan.
Rinse blender with remaining vinegar and add to pepper mixture.
Stir in sugar and red peppers.
Place on high heat and bring to hard boil that cannot be stirred down.
Remove from heat and let stand for 5 minutes.
Skim off foam.
Stir in Certo and coloring.
Mix and pour into hot clean jars and seal (lids or paraffin).
Makes about 7 cups.

title: quick and easy chili dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except chips and simmer together. Serve hot with corn chips.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and vanilla.
Grind pecans in blender.
Add pecans and flour to butter mixture.
Roll into balls and bake 30 minutes at 300°.
Roll twice in confectioners sugar while still warm.

title: rich chocolate cake
directions: Combine cocoa and boiling water, stirring until smooth.
Set aside to cool.
Cream butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla at high speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy, about 5 minutes.
Combine flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with cocoa mixture; beat at low speed, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool completely on wire racks.
Ice with your favorite icing.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Heat oil over medium heat; add onion and cook until soft. Stir in garlic and green pepper.
Saute 2 minutes.
Blend in flour.
Add tomato sauce and cook another 5 minutes.
Stir in water, parsley, shrimp, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Beat together eggs, sugar, oil, buttermilk and vanilla on low speed. Beat in flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into pan.
Bake 1 hour or until a pick inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: raisin cake
directions: Heat butter.
Add eggs, sugar and half of flour; mix well. Add vanilla.
In separate bowl, mix remaining flour and raisins. Add mixture to batter.
Bake at 275° until done.

title: mary pudding hill fruit cake
directions: Beat
eggs;
add sugar and beat again.	Add 1 cup flour and mix well.
Dredge fruit and nuts in 1 cup of flour and add to sugar
and	egg
mixture.
Pour
batter
into
greased and floured pan.
Bake at 250° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix first four ingredients and pour into baking dish over desired fruit.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: pasta and fresh vegetables
directions: Steam fresh vegetables.
In large, heavy frying pan, saute 4 cloves garlic, sliced thin (do not burn).
Add 1/2 large can plum tomatoes, squashing tomatoes in hand.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add steamed veggies.
As soon as they are heated through, top with cooked spaghetti.
Start stirring so spaghetti gets warmed.
Serve immediately.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.

title: microwave chocolate fudge
directions: Cook on High in microwave for 2 minutes.
Prepare an oblong cake pan by buttering sides and bottom.
When done, take from microwave and beat until smooth.
An electric mixer can be used. Add nuts, if desired.
Pour into cake pan; let set in refrigerator for a few hours.
Cut, but keep fudge in refrigerator in an airtight container.

title: black bean salad
directions: Twist crown from pineapple; cut pineapple in half lengthwise. Refrigerate half for another use.
Cut fruit from shell with a knife.
Core and chunk fruit.
In a large bowl, combine pineapple with salad ingredients.
Pour dressing over salad; toss to coat.

title: michelle's fannie mae fudge with raisins
directions: Lightly butter cookie sheet.
In large pot add sugar, milk, butter and vanilla.
Bring to a rolling boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat.
Add 25 marshmallows and stir until smooth. Then add milk chocolate chips, semi-sweet chips and raisins.
Stir until smooth. Nuts can be added but Michelle doesn't like them. Pour onto cookie sheet and refrigerate.

title: maple praline sauce(especially good served warm over pound cake)
directions: Melt butter in small saucepan over low heat.
Add pecans; cook, stirring until lightly browned.
Gradually add sugar, stirring until smooth.
Stir in water and maple syrup.
Bring to boiling; boil, stirring constantly, 1 minute.
Serve warm.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.
Scoop onto bread.

title: calzones
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. On greased baking sheet, unroll pizza dough and cut in half lengthwise. Spread 1/4 cup Ricotta cheese over each half, leaving 1/4-inch edge. Top each half with 1/2 cup Ragu sauce. Fold dough over and seal by pressing edges with a fork. Bake 15 minutes or until brown.

title: "trash" casserole
directions: Peel and cook potatoes in water until soft.
Drain and mash. Set aside.
Brown beef and drain.
In a large casserole dish, put beef on bottom.
Spread onion over beef.
Then spread green beans over.
Then spread tomato soup over.
Then spread mashed potatoes over.
Finally top with cheese.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven until cheese is lightly browned.
Enjoy your dinner with biscuits.

title: oven fried chicken(low carb)
directions: Blend ingredients with fork until well mixed. Makes 2 1/2 cups mix. Keeps indefinitely in Ziploc bag in freezer.

title: pork chops pacifica
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft, but not brown.
Place pork chops on foil in shallow cooking pan.
Put onions and lemon slices on top.
Combine other ingredients.
Pour over chops.
Seal foil and cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve the juice over rice.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream
sugar and oleo, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour in fourths, milk in thirds and add vanilla.
Beat 4 minutes, pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Place
in
a cold oven.
Set oven at 325°.
Bake 1 hour without
opening oven.
At end of hour, set oven at 350° and bake 1/2 hour longer.

title: asparagus and potato loaf
directions: Butter and dust pan.
Beat egg and add to the potato. Pack a layer into the pan using half the potato.
Add layer of asparagus. Finish with potato.
Dust with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes. Unmold and serve with creamed asparagus.
Top with slices of hard-boiled eggs.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cheese until fluffy, beat in peanut butter and sugar. Slowly add milk, mix thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip and pour into crust.
Freeze until firm.

title: prince of peace lutheran church of la crescent apple pie
directions: Cut lard into dry ingredients and store or freeze until making.
Then add 1 1/2 cups ice water with 3 tablespoons vinegar thrown in.

title: chicken aspic salad
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Simmer parsley, onion and celery leaves in chicken broth for 20 minutes.
Add gelatin; strain and cool.
When it begins to set, add lemon juice, chicken and vegetables.
Pour into large or individual molds.
Chill thoroughly.
Unmold.
Garnish with lettuce, parsley and mayonnaise.

title: easy baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Put chops and soup into a covered casserole dish.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Gravy is great over rice.
Can use 2 cans of soup for extra gravy.

title: no-peek casserole
directions: Combine ingredients well in a 2-quart casserole.
Cover.
Bake at 300° for 2 1/2 hours.
Don't peek.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: kentucky pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, eggs, vanilla, salt and butter.
Stir briefly; add chips and nuts.
Pour into crust; bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetarian chopped liver
directions: Saute the onions until limp; add the mushrooms until they are tender and the onion is brown.
Place all the ingredients in the blender, using medium speed until the mixture is smooth.
Season to taste.
Can be made a day ahead and stored in the refrigerator. Delicious on crackers or matzo or served in scoops on a bed of lettuce.
Serves 4 as a first course or makes 2 cups of spread.

title: chicken & rice soup
directions: Strain broth, pour into rice mixture. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: orange or lemon salad
directions: Mix orange or lemon jello, boiling water, juice from pineapple or apricots, apricots and pineapple.
Let set until syrupy, uncovered.
Whip cottage cheese and Cool Whip.
Add to previous mixture.
Fold in pecans; cover and refrigerate.

title: basting sauce (chicken or turkey)
directions: Mix all above ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Baste chicken or turkey cooked on outdoor grill or indoor.
If it is not all used while cooking, it may be used to dip over carved turkey.
Keep moistened.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325 degrees until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Grease and flour cake pans.
Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Blend 1/2 minute on low speed, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat for 3 minutes on high speed.
Pour into pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
(Frosting recipe follows.)

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix cake mix, yeast, eggs, water and flour together.
Let rise until doubled in size.
Roll out in rectangle and spread with melted butter and brown sugar.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Roll up. Slice into 1-inch slices.
Place in greased pan and let double again.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: german potato salad
directions: Wash, then cut the okra into 1/4-inch slices.
Bread with white cornmeal, salt and pepper. Get your liquid oil good and hot. Deep fat fry
until golden brown. The more well done, the more we like it.

title: apple bread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine sugar, salt, soda, cinnamon and flour. Wash, core and peel apples. Chop into small pieces and add to flour mixture. Slightly beat the eggs and mix with oil and vanilla. Stir into flour and apples, mixing well. Pour batter into 2 or 3 medium well-greased loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 1-1 1/2 hours. This recipe will also make about 2 1/2 dozen muffins.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix spinach and lettuce in 9 x 12-inch glass Pyrex bowl. Crumble bacon over spinach.
Slice boiled eggs over bacon, then layer sliced onions and mushrooms.
Mix sour cream and mayonnaise. Toss salad and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Wrap with Saran Wrap and refrigerate.
Make sure spinach and lettuce are dry.

title: gak
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cup water with glue.
Add food coloring.
Mix Borax with water in separate bowl.
Add 1/3 cup Borax mixture to glue mixture; stir well.
Repeat last step 2 times.
Knead Gak until all liquid is absorbed.
Store in airtight container.

title: cucumber pickles from overgrown cucumbers
directions: Rinse well canning lime and water.
Cover with ice water and soak 3 hours.
Drain well.

title: fruit cookie bars
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Spread nuts in bottom of pan.
Mix melted butter with brown sugar, eggs, vanilla flavoring and flour.
Mix together and pour over nuts in pan.
Chop cherries and pineapple and spread over batter.
Cook 1 hour at 300°.
Cut in bars while hot.
(Cook 45 minutes for soft bars.)

title: pickapeppa cream cheese
directions: Place cream cheese in the middle of serving dish.
Cover the cream cheese with the Pickapeppa sauce.
Spread over crackers or whatever you desire.
It's delicious and will soon be your favorite.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding mix and milk at lowest speed on mixer until well blended.
Add Cool Whip and vanilla.
Layer graham crackers and pudding in a 9 x 13-inch pan, beginning with graham crackers. Chill about 1 hour.
Spread frosting over the top.
Refrigerate. Is best to let sit overnight before serving.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Set aside 2/3 cup cake mix.
Combine remaining mix, oleo and beaten egg.
Stir by hand until mixture is crumbly.
Spread mixture evenly over bottom and 1-inch up the sides of ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill for 2 hours. Roll into balls and place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Yield:
50 balls.

title: super bowl cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
Combine crumbs, cocoa, sugar and margarine.
Press firmly on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan; pour Eagle Brand milk evenly over crust.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour into deep dish pie shell.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cowboy soup
directions: Stir-fry
meat and onions in soup pan.
Cook until well done. Add
all
other
ingredients and mix well.
Cook on low heat for 40 minutes.

title: banana chicken salad
directions: Combine bananas and pineapple in bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve in lettuce cups.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: beer muffins
directions: Mix fast. Bake in muffin tin for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix in a sauce pan sugar, cornstarch, water and vinegar. Boil 5 minutes.
Add beets and let stand at least 30 minutes or more.
Just before serving bring to boiling point and add 2 Tbsp. butter.

title: oatmeal hawaiian bread
directions: Combine eggs and sugar.
Beat 2 minutes.
Sift flour.
Add to egg mixture and blend until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Spoon into pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: trader's pie
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain. Set aside.
Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine 1 1/4 cups milk, cream cheese, flour and salts. Cook mixture and stir until smooth.
Beat egg.
Add a little hot mixture to egg and add egg to hot mixture. Let thicken.
Add beef, broccoli and onion.
Pour into a 9-inch pie pan lined with 1 pie crust.
Top with cheese.
Cover with crust. Seal and flute.
Pick top with fork. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix pudding with pineapple juice, then mix with fruit.

title: mints
directions: Cream the cream cheese and add flavoring, color and powdered sugar until desired consistency to mold.
Roll into balls the size of marbles and roll in sugar and mold.
Makes approximately 200 mints.

title: creamy buttermilk dressing
directions: Put buttermilk and cottage cheese in a blender and blend until creamy.
Add seasonings and salt to taste.
Thin, if desired, with more buttermilk.
Keep refrigerated.

title: caramel pudding cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to creamed mixture with milk.
Stir until smooth.
Stir in raisins.

title: lori's quick casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; drain. Cook macaroni and drain. Add everything to a casserole dish and top with cheese. Bake for about 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Crumble ground beef in microwave-safe colander.
Place over bowl to collect drippings.
Microwave on High 5 minutes; drain. Add spaghetti sauce, water and Italian seasonings to cooked beef; set aside.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, milk and butter to soft ball stage, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; mix until well blended.
Pour into buttered pan.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix in order given.
Use more sugar because the lemonade mix is unsweetened.
For 1 cup of tea use about 3 teaspoons of mix.

title: taco dip
directions: Cook sausage; drain off any grease.
Add all other ingredients, except cheese.
Put in baking dish and sprinkle cheese on top. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with taco or burrito chips for dipping.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake mix into 2 layers.
Cool, then split layers in half, making 4 layers.
Cover bottom of punch bowl with 1 layer.
Then layer cherry pie filling, pineapple, pudding, bananas, nuts and Cool Whip until you use all 4 layers, ending with Cool Whip and nuts on top.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk in a large mixing bowl 10 minutes. Add the two meats which have been well mixed, then add egg whites, salt, pepper, mustard and allspice.

title: noodle burritos
directions: Drain noodles and spread out on paper towels.
Crumble ground beef and brown.
Drain grease.
Stir in seasoning mix and water. Stir in beans.
Spread about 1/2 cup of meat mixture down center of each noodle.
Sprinkle one end with cheese.
Starting with cheese end, roll up noodles carefully so filling does not come out. Spread 1/4 cup taco sauce over bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Arrange noodles, seam down, in pan.
Top with remaining taco sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or microwave on High 15 minutes.

title: the best vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs for 10 minutes.
Add other ingredients and beat good after each addition.
Freeze.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix in order given.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: impossible chicken n' broccoli pie(the pie that makes its own crust)
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2-inches). Rinse broccoli under running cold water to thaw; drain thoroughly. Mix broccoli, 2 cups of Cheddar cheese, chicken and onion in pie plate.
Beat milk, eggs, baking mix, salt and pepper.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, 25 to 35 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake just until cheese is melted, 1 to 2 minutes longer.
Cool 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cornbread casserole
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix together and set aside the topping, cream cheese, dill and dry mustard.
Mix Jiffy cornbread mix, eggs, creamed corn and salt to taste.
Spread topping on and sprinkle cheese on top.

title: alex's favorite chicken
directions: Saute chicken in nonstick skillet.
Remove chicken when browned and place in a Dutch oven or stew pot.
Pour Coke over chicken and then add barbecue sauce and ketchup to cover chicken. Texas Pete can be added for a kick.
I shake in 1/2 to 1 teaspoon. Simmer chicken until tender.
Very good served over rice.

title: tabbouleh (cracked wheat salad)
directions: Place bulgar in a large bowl, cover with cold water, let soak for 10 minutes.
Drain, add all ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Serve on lettuce.
Can be used as an appetizer, salad or meal.

title: seven layer vegetable salad
directions: On top spread 1 pint of mayonnaise with 2 tablespoons of sugar added.
Let set overnight, then stir or toss with fork when ready to use.

title: pink ham dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs; blend well.
Add bananas; beat well.
Add flour and soda, beat well after each addition.
Add nuts; mix well.
Pour batter into well-greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and eggs.
Add baking powder, salt and flour.
Blend baking soda, buttermilk and vanilla separately.
Add to first mixture and mix well.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheets for 8 to 10 minutes.
Top with your favorite icing.

title: baked catfish
directions: Combine first seven ingredients; set aside.
Whisk egg white and milk together.
Dip fillets in milk mixture and dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Place on foil-lined baking sheet with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.

title: roast leg of lamb
directions: Wipe
meat
with paper towel.
Make gashes in the meat; place the slivers of garlic in.
Sprinkle roast with rosemary, thyme, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Place in pan, fat side up,
and roast,
uncovered, in slow oven (300°) until tender. Allow	30
to 35
minutes
per pound for roasting.
When meat thermometer registers 180°, the lamb will be well done.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and 1 cup whipped topping; spread on first layer.
Mix pudding and milk; spread on second layer.
Spread whipped topping on the third layer and sprinkle pecans on top. Place in the refrigerator.

title: harvest cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar together. Let stand 1 hour. Stir in rest of ingredients; mix well. Pour in 2 loaf pans or large tube pan. Grease pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or longer until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chili sauce
directions: Grind together tomatoes, onions, green peppers and red pimentos.
Add vinegar, ground cloves, celery seed, brown sugar, coarse salt and red pepper.
Cook until thick and then can.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Rinse chicken breasts and drain well.
Arrange in nonmetal baking dish with meat side down in lemon juice.
Cover and refrigerate 1 hour.
Remove chicken.
Pat dry with paper towels (save marinade).
In a pie plate, beat egg with 1/4 cup marinade.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Saute onion and bell pepper.
Add sausage.
Cook until done. Drain grease off sausage.
Bring chicken broth to a boil.
Pour over rice and sausage mixture in baking dish.
Salt to taste. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: minestrone - meat soup
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add remaining ingredients and heat. Add water for thinner soup.

title: lone star lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients and mix well. Spread in an 8 x 8-inch glass dish and bake for 15 minutes.

title: fruit salad sauce
directions: Mix until smooth.
Pour over a bowl of drained fruit mixture of your choice.
Mix well; mixture will thicken.
Keep refrigerated.
This will keep for a few days and fruit will not turn dark.

title: caramel icing
directions: Brown 1/4 cup sugar separately, while bringing remaining mixture to a boil.
Let boil approximately 8 minutes before adding browned sugar mixture.
Beat by hand or mixer until desired consistency.

title: ham and cheese quiche
directions: Brush pie shell with egg white; refrigerate.
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: microwave peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook on High for 2 minutes (adjust to your microwave).
Add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well and pour in baking dish.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients as listed.	Pour into greased pan.	Bake slowly at 400° or lower for 1 hour.
Check potatoes if done.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown hamburger, onions and peppers.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove cover of casserole for last 15 minutes of cooking time.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: Brown the onion and celery in butter in a heavy skillet. Combine with bread cubes, corn bread and seasonings.
Pour on the broth and stir lightly to blend.
Stuff fowl and roast according to weight of bird.
This amount of dressing is for a 4 1/2 to 5 pound bird.
For larger fowl double the amount.

title: little porcupines
directions: Combine rice, meat, onion and salt.
Form mixture into balls of 1 1/2-inches.
Heat in heavy skillet the tomato juice, cinnamon, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Drop in meat balls. Cover tightly and simmer 50 minutes.

title: meatball stew
directions: Combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, onions and the seasoning. Shape in about 1-inch meatballs.
Brown in oil.
Remove as they brown.

title: divinity
directions: Boil sugar, Karo and water until it forms a hard ball in water. Pour slowly over stiffly beaten egg whites. Beat until ready for vanilla and pecans. Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper and let dry or pour into a greased pan. Let dry. Then cut into squares.

title: best ever cake
directions: Mix together with spoon.
Do not use mixer.
Bake at 350° in 9 x 13 inch greased pan for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: cup custard
directions: Combine ingredients; transfer to six medium size custard cups. Stand cups in pan of warm water and bake in 350° oven until firm and lightly browned, approximately 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine and saute onion.
Mix cornbread mix and eggs with onion and stir.
Place layer of cornbread mix in baking dish, then place deboned chicken on top of cornbread mix.
Mix soups and broth and pour over chicken and cornbread mix.
Sprinkle rest of cornbread mix on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ham delight
directions: Melt margarine or butter.
Add onion powder, poppy seed, mustard powder and Worcestershire.
Cut finger rolls in half; put shaved ham and Swiss in between halves and brush mixture on top. Put back in bag and refrigerate a couple hours.
When ready to serve, bake in oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Or dip shaved ham in mixture; drain excess.
Then make sandwich and pour excess on top.

title: mom's mystery squares
directions: Mix as pastry and place firmly in greased 9 x 9-inch or 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in moderate oven for 10 minutes.

title: pumpkin cheese bread
directions: Mix in a large bowl.
This makes a lot.
Cream butter and sugar; add egg and cream cheese.
Beat well.
Add pumpkin, flour and spices.
Mix well; stir in nuts.
Grease and flour 3 loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans to wire rack.
Bread will crack on top.
It freezes well.

title: quick chicken primavera
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and garlic.
Cook and stir until chicken is no longer pink (3 to 4 minutes).
Add milk and frozen vegetables with pasta. Cover; simmer 4 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender. Stir before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: creamy pumpkin pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Add pumpkin, eggs, butter and milk, mixing well.
Pour into pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked apple custard
directions: Spoon apple pie filling into bottom of 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar and salt.
Mix well.
Scald milk.
Add slowly stirring constantly.
Add vanilla.
Pour over pie filling.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Set in pan of cold water. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Chill.
Serve with any favorite sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: slaw
directions: Mix cabbage, pepper, onion and salt.
Let stand 15 minutes. Drain and add sugar and vinegar.
Put in container and refrigerate.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs.
Add oatmeal, flour, baking powder, soda, vanilla, salt, Rice Krispies and coconut.
Mix.
Roll in small balls and flatten slightly with fork or glass on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: chinese pineapple meatballs
directions: Combine beef, celery, pecans, salt, cornflakes, eggs, soy sauce and garlic.
Roll into small balls.
Roll these in flour and deep fry in very hot vegetable oil, then drain.

title: baked french onion soup
directions: In covered 4-quart saucepan, cook onions slowly in butter and 2 tablespoons oil for 15 minutes; stir occasionally.
Uncover and increase heat to moderate.
Add sugar; saute onions, stirring frequently, about 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with flour.
Stir over heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Blend in hot broth and wine.
Adjust seasonings.
Simmer, partially covered, for 1 hour.

title: turkey and sage polenta cakes
directions: Combine broth, onion, and celery in a large heavy bottom pan. In a small bowl, combine cornmeal and sage.
Stir to mix. Bring broth to a boil.
Reduce heat to simmer and gradually add the cornmeal mixture a half cup at a time, stirring with a wooden spoon. Continue cooking for about 20 minutes or until the mixture is thick and smooth.
It will start to leave a film on bottom and sides of pan.
Remove from heat and stir in butter and cheese. Taste and add salt, if needed. Pour the polenta into a buttered 8 inch square pan.
Allow to cool completely.
Cut the polenta into 2 inch squares.

title: copper pennies
directions: Combine and pour over carrots, onion and peppers.

title: strawberry daiquiri
directions: Fill the blender 1/2 full with crushed ice.
Add remaining ingredients and blend one minute.
Pour into chilled glass. Makes 2 servings.
Other fruit can be used in this way.
Peaches or nectarines can be used.

title: santa fe stew
directions: Brown the meat; drain off fat. Pour meat in a kettle or in crock-pot. Add the Ranch dressing mix, taco seasoning mix and onion. Add the kidney beans, pinto beans, tomatoes and corn. Heat it all together and enjoy.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cukes; sprinkle with salt and bury in ice for at least 3 hours.
Then drain well.
Bring sugar, vinegar and spices to a boil, then add cukes and return to scalding (not boiling).
Cuke will turn different color when ready.
Fill hot jars.
Yields 7 or 8 pints.

title: chiparoni vegetable casserole
directions: Prepare dinner as directed on package, except using 1/2 cup milk.
Add peas and carrots, soup, celery and onion.
Mix lightly.

title: chicken and asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus.
Place on bottom of baking dish.
Mix chicken, celery, water chestnuts and chicken soup.
Top with Pepperidge Farm mixed with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: omelet
directions: Beat all together; put in skillet.
Stir occasionally until done.
Top with cheese.
Serves 7 people.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add rest of the ingredients. Mix well.
Shape as desired.
Bake on cookie sheet for about 20 minutes at 325°.
While hot, roll thumb in powdered sugar.

title: coconut iced cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, dissolve gelatine in 1/2 cup water.
Set aside.
Bring to a boil the sugar and corn syrup.
Pour hot syrup over gelatine mixture; stir to blend.
Cool thoroughly.
Add vanilla.
Beat 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes.
Spoon onto wafers or gingersnaps.
Roll in coconut.

title: poor boy cake
directions: Place first 8 ingredients in boiler.
Cook until thick.
Let cool, then stir in remaining ingredients.
Stir until thick and then spread in a large greased sheet pan.
Bake at 325° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Cake will be done when firm on top.

title: meatless stuffed peppers
directions: Mix together the first five ingredients.
Pour spaghetti sauce in 12-inch skillet.
Stuff green peppers with above mixture. Place in skillet and bring to boil; simmer for 15 minutes.

title: pink salad
directions: Mix first 4
ingredients
together;
fold in Cool Whip. Let set 2 hours in refrigerator.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, vanilla and buttermilk. Sift together flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Add chocolate that has been softened.
Blend together well.
Cook in Bundt pan that has been greased and floured well.
Bake at 300° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.

title: american pierogi
directions: Melt oleo.
Add onions and saute until golden.
In a 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan put alternating layers of macaroni, potatoes and cheese.
Pour melted oleo with onions on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Boil macaroni before beginning recipe.
Serves 8.

title: pancakes devine
directions: The night before:
Mix buttermilk and oatmeal.
Let set overnight.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix together sugar, Karo, butter, vanilla and eggs. Pour over pecans in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chili meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, beat 1/2 cup water with egg yolks.
Stir in bread crumbs, cheese, chili powder and salt. Add chuck; mix with hands.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in shallow pan and bake 12 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika just before serving.

title: no cook barbecue sauce
directions: In bowl, stir together corn syrup and remaining ingredients. Brush on meats or poultry, turning frequently, during last 20 minutes of grilling.
Makes about 1 1/2 cups.

title: pickle relish
directions: Combine chopped vegetables in a large bowl.
Sprinkle with salt and cover with cold water.
Let set for 2 hours; drain and rinse thoroughly.
Combine sugar, vinegar and spices in a pot; bring to a boil.
Add drained vegetables.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Pack in jars. Process in boiling water 10 minutes.

title: pistachio-marshmallow pudding
directions: Beat pudding mix into cold milk and beat with wire whisk 2 minutes. Pour into 2-quart bowl and allow to chill and set. Before serving, add miniature marshmallows and mix well to incorporate. Makes 16 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Cream thoroughly cream cheese and peanut butter.
Mix in milk and sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Put in graham cracker crumb pie crust and freeze.
Serve frozen.

title: microwave company chicken breasts
directions: Cook rice or noodles conventionally while microwaving chicken. Place a slice of chipped beef on each half breast.
Roll up breasts and secure with 4 wooden picks.
Place sliced mushrooms in an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Arrange breasts on top.
Combine soup and sour cream; spoon over chicken.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave 7 1/2 to 12 1/2 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink. Rearrange after half of time cooking.
Sprinkle almonds over chicken.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.
Mix coconut and nuts.
Sprinkle in bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on box.
Pour melted butter over coconut and nuts.
Pour cake mix over the mixture. Cream confectioners sugar and cream cheese together.
Drop by teaspoons on batter.
Cook at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: cheese straws
directions: Cream margarine.
Add cheese.
Work in flour and red pepper. When well mixed, fill cookie press and press out on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients, beating as you go.
Bake in iron skillet, heated with bacon grease, at 400° until good and brown (about 30 minutes).

title: overnite cookies
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Beat sugar in a little at a time. Beat until it stands in peaks. Add vanilla, salt, nuts and chips. Put foil on pan.
Put cookie with teaspoon on the foil-lined pan. Heat oven to 350°.
Put cookies in oven and turn off heat.
Leave in overnight.
Makes 30 minutes.
Very good and pretty.

title: noodles
directions: Cook noodles and pour water off. Cook all this in another pan. Pour over together. Put in oven and bake until brown a little. Then ready to eat.

title: everlasting slaw
directions: Chop cabbage and carrot.
Soak both in ice water to which the salt was added.
Boil sugar, vinegar and water for 1 minute.
Drain cabbage.
Add the syrup.
Place in refrigerator.
Keeps for days.

title: fried hot banana peppers
directions: Cut the tops off of the banana peppers and clean out the seeds.
Mix the eggs up in one dish and the flour in a separate dish.
Put 3 to 4 pieces of cheese inside the pepper, dip in egg, then flour and fry in butter.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and blend all ingredients together.
Bake in a greased pan at 400° until done.
Cut into squares.

title: split seconds
directions: Mix together to form dough.
Divide into 4 parts.
Shape into long rolls.
Place onto ungreased baking sheet and make depression in the rolls.
Fill with jelly.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. After cooled, cut into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Bread should be torn into 1/4-inch size pieces.
Toss bread with drained pineapple.
Place in a greased 2-quart baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan).
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over pineapple.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes (uncovered).
Can be made and refrigerated overnight before baking.
Very good with ham. Serves 10 to 12.

title: chicken breast
directions: This may be cooked on top of the stove or baked. I add a little water after the chicken has browned and cover for a few minutes to steam. Then uncover and continue cooking. A side dish of rice and a salad makes a light dinner/supper.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick oleo with cracker crumbs; press in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Set aside.
Beat 10 minutes eggs, oleo (room temperature) and powdered sugar.
Spread on graham cracker crust.
Add layer of sliced bananas, layer of pineapple, Cool Whip and nuts.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Roll nuts in this mixture until coated.
Put sugar, cinnamon and salt in a bowl and mix well.
Take the nuts from the egg mixture and roll in sugar mixture.
Place on a buttered pan and bake at 225 degrees for 1 hour, stirring often.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Mix together the powdered sugar, cocoa, butter and milk. Microwave on High for 2 minutes. Stir, then add vanilla and nuts. Stir again.
Pour into a 10 x 8-inch dish that has been well-greased.
Refrigerate for 2 hours before cutting.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil and cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Mix sour cream, soup and poppy seed.
Pour over chicken.
May salt if needed.
Top with crushed crackers.
Pour on melted butter and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sausage risotto dish
directions: Brown sausage, drain. Add onions, cook until tender. Stir in water and oregano; bring to full boil. Stir in rice and parsley. Cover, remove from heat. Let stand 5 minutes; fluff with fork. Stir in process cheese food until melted.

title: nacho cheese soup
directions: In large pot, combine potatoes, corn, picante sauce and water. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 25 minutes, until potatoes are tender.
Add dry cheese, olives and taco cheese. Cook heated through, stirring occasionally.
Serve with chips. Makes 8 cups.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix all fruit together with marshmallows. Fold in Cool Whip.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well and pack into a loaf pan.
Spread catsup over top. Scrub potatoes and rub them with shortening.
Bake loaf and potatoes in a hot 400° oven for one hour.

title: zippy beef casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook meat until brown; drain off fat. Cook macaroni as directed on the package and drain.
In ungreased 2-quart casserole dish, mix all ingredients.
Cover and bake for 45 minutes.

title: easy yellow cake
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk, margarine and vanilla.
Beat with a mixer for 2 minutes.
Add eggs; beat for 2 more minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.
Bake in a 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes, or until done.
Cool 10 minutes.
Makes 12 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of casserole dish.
Combine soup, mayonnaise, margarine, onion and eggs.
Pour over broccoli.
Top with cheese and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 20 minutes and serve.

title: stuffed chile peppers
directions: Roast peppers on a skillet until well toasted.
Let them cool. Peel the crust off peppers; cut a slice off top of each pepper and scoop out insides.
Fill with slices of cheese, tomatoes and onions.
Whip up egg whites well, then add egg yolks and whip until foams up.
Dip stuffed chile peppers in the eggs and fry in a large frying pan in heated oil until slightly brown.

title: bugs on a log
directions: Cut celery into short pieces.
Spread peanut butter on the celery.
Place raisins across the top.

title: chinese chicken wings
directions: If possible, skin chicken wings.
Combine all ingredients and add wings.
Marinate for 30 minutes.
Wings can be cooked in a 350° oven until done or on stove top with scallions.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat again, then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Pie is done when inserted knife blade comes out clean.

title: walding family ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add condensed milk and mix well.
Add flour to sugar and add to mixture.
Add milk and flavoring.

title: easy marinated mushrooms
directions: In large saucepan, bring dressing and mushrooms to a boil. Cook uncovered for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add lemon peel, juice, pimento and parsley.
Cover and chill for at least four hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut round steak in serving pieces.
Pound flour, salt and pepper into meat and brown in frying pan.
Chill and refrigerate until morning.
Place in casserole and place sliced onion and celery over top.
Add a small can of steak sauce mixed with same amount of water.
Bake 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 325°.

title: pepper relish
directions: Chop (not grind) peppers and onions.
Cover with boiling water and let stand for 5 minutes; drain.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt and bring to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Pour into sterilized jars and seal.
Yields 7 pints.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix with mixer.
First mix pudding, milk and vanilla flavoring until thick.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Then, in a sheet pan, spread the bottom of pan with a layer of graham crackers.
Then add 1/2 of pudding mixture, layer of graham crackers, then another layer of pudding and another layer of graham crackers.

title: cornbread
directions: Stir together cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. Mix milk and eggs together.
Add to dry ingredients.
Melt butter.
Pour into cornmeal mixture.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Bake at 400°.

title: countryman's cranberry salad
directions: Cook cranberries, 2 cups water and sugar together until cranberries are soft.
Measure and add enough water to make 4 cups.
Add cherry jello and stir until dissolved.
When thick, add apples and celery.
Pour into mold.
When chilled, put Golden Dressing on top.

title: cherry cobbler(cobblers are a very tasty dessert.)
directions: In a bowl, mix all ingredients and place in a baking dish so dough is about 1/2-inch thick.
(There is enough dough for two; or second half can be used as a cover and cherry glaze is baked inside similar to a pie.)

title: troy aikman corn
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute squash with onion in 2 tablespoons of margarine.
Combine squash, onion, sour cream, 1 cup of cheese, salt and pepper.
Spoon into greased casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and cracker crumbs; pour remaining 2 tablespoons margarine over top.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: tony's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all.
Brush on meat, fish or poultry, approximately 1/2 hour before done.

title: john's chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onions and pepper.
Pour off any excess juice.
Add celery, tomatoes and kidney beans.
Cook slowly for 30 minutes or more.
Simmer on low for 30 minutes longer.
Then add chili powder.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil first three ingredients for three minutes after it comes to a rolling boil.
Add next three ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13 buttered pan.
Cool, cut.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix ingredients and pour in 9 x 13-inch glass dish.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: kitchen sink salad
directions: Cook, rinse and cool macaroni.
Chop onion, celery, peppers and shave carrots with vegetable peeler.
Drain olives. Cut up hard-boiled eggs.
Mix all ingredients together. Add mayonnaise to moisten. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: skillet spaghetti
directions: In 12-inch skillet, brown ground beef; drain off excess fat. Stir in chili powder, oregano, sugar, salt and garlic salt.
Blend in tomato paste.
Stir in tomato juice, onion and 3 1/2 cups water.
Bring to a boil.
Carefully add spaghetti; stir to separate strands.
Cover and simmer, stirring frequently, for 30 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: marinated eggs
directions: Place eggs in water.
Boil to hard-cooked.
Peel shell.
Pack in hot sterilized jars.
In saucepan, bring to boil vinegar, sugar, salt, spice and onion.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Strain and pour over eggs.
Cover and let stand 1 to 2 days to marinate.

title: booze cake
directions: Boil the raisins in 1 1/2 cups water for 20 minutes.
Should be 3/4 cup liquid when done. Separate juice from raisins and cool. Cream the sugar and butter. Add egg and keep on beating. Alternately add flour, spices and liquid until well mixed.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Bake in a 9-inch square greased pan or 7 x 11-inch pan at 350° until done. Frost with plain butter frosting.

title: tater soup
directions: Boil potatoes, onion, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Boil until it's mushy.
Keep adding water and stirring.
Drain and add butter. Use potato masher and start adding milk.
Mash until there are small chunks left.
Finish adding milk and reheat.

title: white fudge
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients
to a firm ball, slightly above 240°.
Add 1 tablespoon butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Cool, beat and add nuts or chopped maraschino cherries.
This gets white.

title: coleslaw
directions: Combine first seven ingredients. Set aside.
Combine chopped ingredients.
Add dressing and stir well.
Garnish with paprika, if desired.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Fold in crushed pineapple and bread.
Bake in buttered bread pan at 350°F for 40-60 minutes.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Cook ground beef until brown.
Drain.
Spread in baking dish. Top with pizza sauce and cheese.
Combine Bisquick mix, milk and eggs.
Beat until smooth.
Pour over casserole.
Cover entirely. Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: david warren's candied yams
directions: Boil the potatoes
in water to cover until tender. Drain and cool slightly.
Peel and cut in quarters.
Place in long, shallow baking dish. Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon. Cut butter in thin slivers and distribute over surface.
Pour in water, then sprinkle sugar and salt over all. Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: baked grits
directions: Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
This is for 100.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Mix and pour over ingredients in a Pyrex dish or mix with the pineapple mixture.
Bake 35 minutes at 400°.

title: rona's cabbage noodles
directions: Precook bacon; remove. Use grease to cook cabbage and onions. Add salt, pepper and soy sauce. Toss with precooked noodles.

title: mother's fruit cake cookies
directions: Chop fruit and nuts. Dredge in 1 cup flour. Cream butter and sugar; add egg yolks. Mix well. Add 2 cups flour, spices and buttermilk. Then add fruit and nuts with the flour it was dredged in. Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites and drop by rounded teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
