title: cathy's bacon wrapped potatoes
directions: Take new red potatoes (small) and cut into 4 or 6 pieces or wedges.
Wash potatoes first and do not peel.
Roll potato pieces in equal amounts of seasoned salt and seasoned pepper.
Take a slice of bacon and cut in half, then cut each half again lengthwise (4 pieces).
Wrap bacon around potato and place on baking sheet. You do not need to use a toothpick to hold bacon on the potato. Bake in 375° oven for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Check time for doneness.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, baking powder, nuts and raisins and set aside.
Mix oil, eggs, sugar and apples together until well blended.
Gradually add dry ingredients until blended.
Pour into greased and floured cake pan (I use Bundt pan).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Boil eggs in cold water.
Add 1 tablespoon salt for easy peeling.
Bring to rolling boil for 3 minutes.
Cut off heat.
Let set.
Drain off hot water, then peel in cold water.
Split peeled eggs in half.
Remove yolks from whites.
Press yolks with potato masher.

title: easy custard
directions: Mix all ingredients for 2 minutes.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat well until smooth.
Add small amount of yellow food coloring.
Pour mixture into cooled pie shell.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions on package.
Using a 9 x 13-inch pan, put half of batter into pan and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
While this is baking, in a saucepan over low heat, combine caramel candy, margarine and milk, stirring until melted.
Remove cake from oven and pour mixture over cake; sprinkle chocolate morsels and nuts over caramel mixture.
Then add remainder of batter.
Return to oven and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple.
Measure liquid.
Add enough water to make 1 cup.
Add to jello.
Stir in blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart flat pan and refrigerate until set.
Combine sugar, sour cream, cream cheese and vanilla.
Spread over jello layer.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
May be used as salad or dessert.

title: strawberry angel dessert
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water and chill until slightly thickened.
Sprinkle sugar over sliced strawberries. Blend whipped topping into thickened gelatin, then fold in cake cubes and strawberries.
Spoon into a 10-inch tube pan and chill until firm, at least 3 hours.
Unmold onto serving plate.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and fresh strawberries.

title: rosemary dressing
directions: Put all ingredients into a jar and shake.
Let stand 24 hours before using.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: In a large bowl, add and mix first 7 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for one hour in two greased loaf pans (knife in center should be dry).

title: kentucky burgoo
directions: Kindle a good hardwood fire in a shallow pit in an open space, free from overhanging trees.
Combine water and seasonings in a large cast-iron pot; bring to a full boil.
Add pork, beef, venison, possum, ground hog, raccoons and onions.
Cook at a low boil for 2 to 3 hours.
Add chicken, rabbits, game birds (whatever amount available) and corn.
Allow fire to burn low enough to maintain a good simmer for 8 to 10 hours, stirring occasionally with a wooden ladle (a boat paddle works well).
Avoid sticking; if ladle will stand upright in mixture, add water.
Stir in liquor for flavor.
The ingredients should cook to pieces with bones settling to the bottom during the last 6 hours of cooking time.
Clear pot of bones and gristle.
When 4 hours remain, add tomatoes, potatoes, beans and celery.
Continue vigorous simmer, stirring until vegetables are thoroughly mixed.
Check for consistency, adding water to thin or cooking down for thicker stew.
Use cornmeal to prepare scalded cornbread.
Makes 50 servings.

title: taco pie(mexican lasagna)
directions: Cut all ingredients approximately in half!

title: diet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until done.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water. Simmer in same water until tender, 1 to 2 hrs. Drain, save bean stock. Heat oven to 300°. Place beans, pork, and onion in 2 qt. casserole in layers. Combine molasses and seasonings; pour over beans. Add enough bean stock to cover. Cover. Bake 8 hrs. Remove cover last half of baking, add a little boiling water if beans seem dry. Yields 6 servings.

title: sweet-n-sour meatballs
directions: Mix ground beef, eggs, salt, pepper and onion.
Shape into small balls.
Heat chili sauce, water and jelly in covered pan. Drop meatballs in sauce after balls have been cooked and drained. Simmer in sauce about 30 minutes or more.

title: pattie scherer's linguine salad
directions: Cook linguine al dente.
Rinse in cold water.
Combine remaining ingredients with linguine. Chill and enjoy! Great with barbecued chicken.

title: ham wrap-ups
directions: Put cream cheese, olives, mayonnaise and mustard in blender and run on puree until smooth. Spread mixture thinly on ham slices; roll each slice as for jelly roll.
Wrap in aluminum foil and chill for several hours.
Slice in 1/4-inch slices and serve on Ritz crackers.
Makes 25 to 30 appetizers.

title: james ouellette's apple bread
directions: Combine margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add egg; set aside. Mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon. Stir in apple.
Add to first mixture alternately with milk. Transfer to oiled 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely before eating.

title: layered lemon crumb bars
directions: Combine sweetened condensed milk, ReaLemon and rind; set aside.
In large bowl, beat butter and brown sugar until fluffy. Add flour, oats, baking powder and salt; mix until crumbly.
Press half the oat mixture on bottom of lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with lemon mixture.
Stir spices into remaining crumb mixture; sprinkle evenly over lemon layer.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; chill.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: tuna pat
directions: Blend softened cream cheese with all ingredients.
Smooth oil or salad dressing on sides of a 2-cup mold.
Press ingredients into mold.
Chill 3 hours.
Best if chilled overnight.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: beef tips on noodles
directions: Brown meat in about 2 tablespoons of oil; drain.
Mix with other ingredients and put in 3-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over egg noodles.

title: frozen peanut butter pie
directions: Press miniature chocolate chips on crust.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy; add sugar.
Beat well.
Add peanut butter.
Stir in milk.
Add vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour into prepared crust.
Top with chopped peanuts.
Freeze 4 hours.
Let thaw a few minutes before serving.
Very rich, but oh so good!

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook the cut up carrots in water until tender.
When done, let them cool, then add sour cream, mayonnaise and horseradish. Sprinkle the bread crumbs mixed with oleo over the top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 2-quart casserole dish.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°. Lightly grease a 9 1/4 x 5 1/4 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pan with 1 teaspoon of the butter. Line the bottom of the pan with parchment paper. Puree the bananas, sour cream, eggs and vanilla in a food processor. If a food processor is not available, mash with a potato masher. Sift the cake flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt into the bowl of an electric mixer with a whisk attachment. Add the remaining 10 tablespoons butter and mix on medium-low speed until blended, about 30 seconds. Add the banana mixture in batches, scraping the sides of the bowl and mixing on medium speed between each addition. Fold in the nuts. Pour into the loaf pan. Bake until lightly browned and bread bounces back to the touch, about 1 hour and 10 minutes. Remove from the oven and cool for 10 minutes before turning out onto wire rack to cool completely.

title: potato soup
directions: Cut potatoes and onion in bite size pieces. Cover with water; boil until tender.
Add oleo and Season-All.
Put in blender and puree until soup is smooth.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix peaches, 2/3 cup sugar and flour in casserole dish.
Lay slices of trimmed white loaf bread on top of peaches.
Next mix eggs, 1 cup sugar and margarine and pour over bread and peach mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss steak
directions: Place ingredients into crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours. Serve over mashed potatoes.

title: ham and cheese roll-ups
directions: In small bowl combine cheeses and margarine until well blended. Spread 1/4 of mixture on each ham slice.
Roll up from short side; chill several hours.

title: chocolate cherry cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° and grease and flour pan.
Combine all ingredients and mix by hand.
Stir until well mixed.
Pour into pan and bake 20 to 30 minutes.

title: rockport hash
directions: Brown all together the ground chuck, green pepper, onion and chili powder; drain off fat.
Add rice, tomatoes, celery and sugar.
Combine together and place in casserole.
Bake at 350° until tender.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix well and store in refrigerator. Serve chilled.

title: pink stuff
directions: Empty Cool Whip into a large bowl.
Stir in cottage cheese. Drain juice out of pineapple.
Add pineapple to mixture, along with the box of strawberry Jell-O.
Mix well.
Cover and chill.

title: raspberry loaf
directions: Cream sugar and oleo together.
Stir in beaten eggs, milk, fruit and lemon juice.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: beet jelly
directions: Add jello to the juice before adding sugar.

title: top stove cookies(best when a child helps!)
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa in a saucepan.
Bring to a rolling boil and continue to cook for 5 minutes, while being stirred by the child of your choice.
Remove from heat.
While the parent stirs, the child adds the vanilla, oats and peanut butter. Mix well.
All "cooks" use a teaspoon to drop hot mixture onto wax paper.
Cool.
"Cooks" get to test cookies first!

title: honey glazed cinnamon ring
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease bottom and sides of 12-cup Bundt cake pan.
Arrange 8 rolls, cut side down, in bottom of pan. Combine sugar, 1/3 cup honey, nuts, butter, cinnamon and the icing from one can of rolls.
Spread mixture over rolls.
Stagger remaining 8 rolls over the sugar-honey mixture.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until golden brown.
Immediately loosen edges and invert pan to remove coffee cake.
Cool 5 minutes, then combine 2 tablespoons honey and remaining container of icing.
Drizzle over cake.

title: country herb roasted chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a 13 x 9-inch pan, arrange chicken. In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients and brush on chicken.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Use heavy duty Reynolds Wrap, large enough to seal meat and other ingredients.

title: corn relish
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, salt, celery seed, mustard seed and pepper sauce.
Put in a medium saucepot.
Heat over medium heat until boiling; stir.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate at least 2 days to blend flavors.

title: pickled carrots
directions: For marinating mixture, mix the ingredients. Pour over carrots and chill for several hours.

title: day ahead banana pudding
directions: Mix vanilla pudding with milk.
Add sour cream and condensed milk.
Fold in whipped topping.
In large bowl or 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish, layer wafers and bananas.
Add pudding.
Repeat layers. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter and mix well with stuffing mix.
Put 1/2 of this mixture in the bottom of a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Reserve the rest for topping.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Melt butter and saute onions for 5 minutes.
Add celery, salt, pepper and chicken broth.
Cover and cook for 5 minutes.
Add Chinese vegetables.
Mix.
Heat to boiling point.
Add mushrooms and water chestnuts, if desired.
Add thickening made of water, cornstarch, soy sauce, sugar and gravy sauce and cook 1 minute. Add chicken and remove from heat.
Serve over rice with chow mein noodles.

title: beer muffins
directions: Grease muffin tins and warm slightly in 400° oven.
Mix all ingredients and fill muffin tins 2/3 full.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Spray an 8-inch square pan with cooking nonstick spray.

title: mississippi corn bread
directions: Combine eggs with oil.
Stir in corn and then sour cream until blended.
Stir in meal, blending well.
Fold in onions.
Turn mixture into a greased 8-inch square baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: linda's enchiladas
directions: Heat tomato soup with 1 can water in small skillet; turn heat down to simmer.
Put tortillas individually into soup to warm and soften, then remove and place on plate.
Put tablespoonful of onion and cheese mixture on tortilla and roll up.
Place in deep oven pan and repeat until all tortillas are used.
Save back some of onion and cheese mixture to sprinkle on top.
Have chili heating on stove and when all tortillas are filled, rolled and placed in pan, pour chili over all and sprinkle onion and cheese mixture on top.
Warm in oven until cheese is melted.
Serve with refried beans and Spanish rice.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef and drain off fat.
Add chopped onion and chili powder.
Add chili mix.
Cook for 1 hour.
The longer it is cooked the better the taste.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk and shortening.
Beat until smooth.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into greased 8-inch round or square pan or cornbread skillet.
Bake at 425° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: zucchini rice casserole
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease shallow 2-quart casserole dish. In skillet, heat oil and onion until tender.
Add garlic and zucchini; heat on medium-high until zucchini releases juices. Sprinkle with flour and stir one minute, until absorbed.
Stir in half and half, rice, 3/4 cup cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour into dish.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes, until golden and bubbly.
Let stand 10 to 20 minutes to set.

title: party pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese, Miracle Whip and picante sauce.
Heat; beat lightly.
Add green onion and olives.
Spread over tortilla shells and roll into a log.
Chill.
Slice into 1-inch pieces before serving.

title: garlic soup with greens
directions: In large pot, add oil, garlic, onions, bay leaves, thyme, allspice and stock; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until garlic is tender, about 10 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Remove onion and garlic to blender with a small amount of stock; blend until smooth.
Then add garlic and onion mixture to the stock in the pot; heat over low heat while adding milk.
Stir until hot. Add spinach; stir briefly, then serve.
(The hot soup will blanch the spinach.)
Yield: 4 servings.

title: super chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Cut 4 squares of the chocolate into 1/2-inch chunks; set aside. Beat margarine, sugars, egg and vanilla until light and fluffy. Mix in flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in chocolate chunks and walnuts.
Refrigerate at least 30 minutes.

title: seafood frittata
directions: Melt butter in 10-inch ovenproof skillet.
Saute onion with herbs, about 1 minute.
Drain tuna and add to skillet, stirring to break-up big pieces.
Beat eggs well with garlic and pepper.
Pour into pan.
Do not stir.
Cook in oven on medium heat until bottom half of eggs are cooked.
Place under broiler, about 4 inches from heat until eggs are set.
Serve hot.
Cut into wedges.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Fold yogurt and Cool Whip together.
Put in cooled crust and chill.
Cut and serve.

title: coconut pie
directions: Note:
Use numbers in parenthesis to make 5 pies instead of 2.

title: peanut butter sugar cookies
directions: Cream well the first 3 ingredients.
Add egg and vanilla and beat well.
Fold in dry sifted ingredients and mix well.
Work well with hands and form into loaf.
Wrap in waxed paper and store in refrigerator overnight or longer; no longer than 1 week.
Bake on slightly greased sheet at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: easy applesauce meatballs
directions: Mix beef, corn flakes, applesauce, salt and pepper.
Make fist size balls.
Mix catsup and water.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt oleo in pan.
Mix all other ingredients.
Pour over oleo. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Cream yolks and butter; beat in Cool Whip and powdered sugar. Crush candy bars and add to Cool Whip mixture (save enough crushed candy to sprinkle on top of dessert).
Put layer of cake in pan; next, put a layer of Cool Whip mixture.
Continue to layer, ending up with Cool Whip mixture.
Sprinkle remaining crushed candy on top.

title: cucumber and feta salad
directions: Combine cucumber, onion slices, olives and cheese in a bowl. Toss gently to mix.
Stir oil, vinegar, pepper and salt to taste in a cup.
Pour dressing over cucumber mixture and set aside for 10 minutes for flavors to blend.

title: breakfast cookies
directions: Mix softened margarine, sugar, egg and vanilla.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix in Cheddar cheese, oatmeal and wheat germ.
Add bacon strips.
Spoon onto ungreased (no-stick) cookie sheet by the tablespoonful.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes. Cool.
Makes 2 dozen cookies.

title: busha's cheesecake
directions: Mix and pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and set aside.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
In hot oven, bring to boil, then reduce heat and cook 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: nutty banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, one at a time, and cream a few minutes.
Add bananas.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt 3 times.
Add to batter gradually.
Add vanilla and nuts. Bake in a well-greased and floured loaf pan at 300° for 1 hour and another 15 minutes at 275°.

title: corny casserole
directions: Beat eggs.
Melt butter in casserole pan.
Then add eggs into butter mixture.
Beat until mixed.
Then add rest of ingredients. Bake in same casserole pan.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese.
Then bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: calico cabbage
directions: In hot oil, in wok or heavy skillet, stir-fry onion and peppers until onion is golden, about 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes. Stir-fry 2 minutes.
Add cabbage, salt and hot pepper sauce. Simmer, covered, over low heat until cabbage is crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate banana pudding pie
directions: Microwave chocolate, milk and margarine in medium microwave bowl on High, 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir until chocolate is completely melted.
Spread evenly in crust. Refrigerate 30 minutes or until chocolate is firm.
Arrange banana slices over chocolate.
Pour milk into large bowl and add pudding mix.
Beat with wire beater 1 minute.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Spoon over bananas.
Spread with whipped topping.
Refrigerate 4 hours.

title: low-fat fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple (save juice to pour over bananas and apples to keep from turning).
Mix all ingredients and refrigerate.

title: banana rama
directions: Combine in a blender until smooth.

title: apple pie smoothie
directions: In a blender, combine all ingredients.
Blend until smooth. Drink and enjoy.

title: peppermint patties
directions: Shape into patties and freeze, then dip in chocolate.

title: pickled pineapple slices
directions: In large skillet combine pineapple syrup (add water if needed), sugar, vinegar and cinnamon stick.
Bring to boil.
Add pineapple slices and cloves.
Bring back to boil.
Remove from heat and cool completely.
Store in tight container and refrigerate.
Keeps up to 2 weeks.

title: hawaiian pork chops
directions: In crock-pot, place enough pork chops for your family.
Pour pineapple over pork chops.
Sprinkle brown sugar over chops.
Add soy sauce.
Cook on high until chops are tender.

title: poor boy supper
directions: Place hamburger in baking
dish.
Add rice on top, then sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Mix soup and water until smooth and pour
over
top
of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until rice is done.

title: crabmeat canapes
directions: Combine butter, cheese spread and mayo until smooth. Add salt, pepper and crabmeat. Spread mixture on muffins.
Cut into fourths and place on cookie sheet.
Freeze in large Baggie until ready to use. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except croutons, butter and cheese.
Pour in bowl on top of 1/2 the croutons.
Add remaining half of croutons on top.
Melt 1/2 stick of butter and pour on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Add grated cheese the last 5 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar thoroughly.
Add flour with nuts.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Chill until firm.
Bake in a 325° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Shake in a bag of powdered sugar while still warm.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Saute pepper and onion in heated oil in a covered skillet. Blend cornstarch in small amount of chicken broth and set aside. Add remaining broth and soy sauce to skillet, then add chicken or turkey.
Thicken with remaining broth mixture and add tomato wedges.
Serve with white rice.
Serves 4.

title: turnip soup
directions: Put a piece of very lean and boneless fresh pork in a large soup pot and cover with water.
Salt and pepper to taste and cook until pork is tender enough to shred.
In pork broth, with the shredded pork, add peeled and diced turnip roots and one onion that has been chopped.
Finish filling pot with water, to cover the roots.
Cook until roots are very tender.
With a potato masher, mash up a bit, and sprinkle a tablespoon or two of cornmeal over top of soup and stir well.
This will thicken it.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil sweet potatoes in water to cover until tender.
Drain and peel while hot.
Mash until smooth.
Add butter, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla and beat until light and fluffy.
Transfer to a well-buttered casserole dish.

title: ham and cheese party rolls
directions: Combine butter, mustard, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Spread mixture on both sides of rolls (which have been sliced all at once with a long sharp knife).
Put a layer of ham and top with layer of cheese between the sliced rolls.
Place back in foil pan (wrap in foil).
Heat at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes. Freezes well.
Yields 40 rolls.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix in order.
Spoon batter into 3 well-greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cook in pans on a rack for 10 minutes.
Turn cakes out on racks.
Cool and frost.

title: fresh broccoli salad(prepare salad one day before serving)
directions: Mix all ingredients except the bacon and place in a crystal bowl.
Cover and marinate in the refrigerator overnight. Before serving, sprinkle the top of the salad with the crumbled bacon. Serves 6.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain juices off all fruit.
Mix all together in bowl and refrigerate.

title: amazin raisin cake
directions: In large bowl with low speed beat first 10 ingredients 2 minutes (batter will be thick).
With spoon, stir in apples, raisins and nuts.
Bake in two 9-inch cake pans at 235°.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Cool, fill and frost with 2 cups whipped cream.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and cook over low heat until onion is done.
Mix the chicken cube and water; mix in the flour.
Put in onion and butter. Drop broccoli pieces in.
Beat the eggs and pour all into dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs and butter on top. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken breasts in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Top with cheese slices. Combine soup and milk; stir well. Spoon sauce over chicken; sprinkle with stuffing mix. Drizzle butter over crumbs; cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: cinnamon sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to a boil and let thicken.
Remove from heat and add butter and 1/2 teaspoon of vanilla.
Delicious over gingerbread.

title: sweet potato muffins
directions: If using fresh sweet potatoes, cook and mash them without adding anything. If using canned, drain and mash without adding anything.
Combine ingredients, mixing as little as possible. Mix only until all ingredients are mixed together. Pour into greased muffin pans and bake 28-30 minutes at 350°.

title: beefy v-8 soup
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Add remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Simmer until vegetables are tender.
Yields 4 servings.

title: indian house banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Stir in other ingredients by hand.
Pour into buttered loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: morning shake
directions: In the container of electric blender, place milk, banana, orange juice and vanilla.
Cover and whirl until smooth.
Serve at once.
Makes 2 servings of 1 cup each.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Combine
bread, onion, apple and seasoning.
Add butter and hot
water
to moisten.
Fill pork chop pockets with bread stuffing.
Place
on top rack in oven and bake uncovered for 1 hour 15 minutes at 375°.

title: special meat loaf
directions: Mix together and press into squares or rectangular baking pan. Cook for about 45 minutes at 325°. Turn heat up for about 15 minutes to brown.

title: strawberry freezer jam
directions: Wash and hull strawberries. Crush. Place in large bowl. Add sugar and mix well. In a saucepan, combine water and pectin. Bring to boil and boil 1 minute, stirring constantly. Stir into fruit mixture. Continue stirring 3 minutes. Quickly ladle into sterilized jars. Cover with tight lids. Allow to set at room temperature 24 hours. Store in freezer. Makes 6 medium jelly glasses. If kept in the refrigerator, use within 3 weeks.

title: tabooley(tabouli)
directions: Finely chop the scallions, parsley, tomatoes, celery and cucumbers.
In a large crock, place layer of wheat. Add olive oil and lemon juice.
Layer the veggies in order listed, scallions first, cucumbers last.
Sprinkle vegetable salt on top.
Cover crock loosely and store in refrigerator until ready, 24 hours to 2 weeks. Toss well to mix. Check seasoning.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cheeseburger loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix lightly.
Put mixture into a loaf pan and bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Garnish with 5 to 6 strips of American cheese and return to oven for 2 minutes or until cheese melts.
Let stand on a wire rack 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: bananas foster ii
directions: In a large, deep skillet over medium heat, melt butter.
Stir in sugar, rum, vanilla and cinnamon.
When mixture begins to bubble, place bananas and walnuts in pan.
Cook until bananas are hot, 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve at once over vanilla ice cream.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients and add the cake mix and pudding.
Mix together until smooth.
Stir in the chocolate chips. Pour into buttered Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, sift powdered sugar over top.

title: mashed potatoes(makes 6 servings)
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes as directed on package, substituting cream cheese for butter. Stir in onions and parsley. Spoon into 1-quart baking dish. Dot with butter. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: barbecued wieners
directions: Make a sauce with all the ingredients except the wieners. Cook sauce over medium heat until it thickens. Add the wieners and put in baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place on hot dog buns and enjoy. A very good dish to take on a picnic.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and press 2/3 into 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt remaining ingredients over low heat.
Pour over cake mixture in pan.
Drop reserved 1/3 cake mixture in small amounts over filling.
Bake in 350 oven for 25 minutes (do not overbake).

title: mocha cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put ingredients in bowl one by one. Beat with electric mixer 2 to 4 minutes, batter will be thin. Grease 9 x 13-inch pan or two round pans with margarine and then dust with flour.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Test for doneness with a toothpick or a cake tester.
Always test cake in the center of the cake.

title: capital punishment chile
directions: Simmer at least 2 hours.
One-half hour before serving, add 1/2 cup masa, mixed with water to a paste.

title: "sarah's" refrigerator cookies
directions: Cream together sugars and butter.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Add flour and stir in pecans.
Divide dough into 3 parts; form into rolls and wrap in waxed paper, plastic wrap or aluminum foil. Refrigerate.
Slice and bake in 350° oven until brown.

title: prune cake
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and shortening together.
Add all the other ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: end of garden soup
directions: Put all vegetables and water in a large soup kettle and simmer for five minutes.
Pack into hot, sterilized jars.
Seal and process in a pressure cooker at 10 pounds pressure for 70 minutes. Remove and cool before storing in a dark place.
Yields 12 to 14 quarts.

title: popover pizza
directions: Place cooked sausage in 13x9x2 inch pan.
Pour In sauce and mix.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Combine eggs, oil, milk, flour, and salt; beat with mixer until smooth.
Pour over cheese. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 400 degrees for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Do not season with salt as sodium content of broth and chicken soup will add needed flavoring.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar together.
Beat Dream Whip and mix with cheese and sugar on high speed. Top with cherries and chill.

title: cholesterol-free banana raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In a large bowl, mix flour, brown sugar, baking powder and baking soda. Cut in corn oil spread until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in bananas, raisins, oats, egg substitute, applesauce and vanilla extract just until flour is moistened.
Spoon batter into pan. Bake 1 1/4 hours until done.
To prevent overbrowning, cover bread loosely with a tent of foil after 1 hour.
Cool bread in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: dirt cake
directions: You will need 1 new flowerpot (8 1/4-inches in diameter).

title: onion celeste
directions: Cook onions in butter (covered, cook slowly 30 minutes). Spoon in baking dish.
Spread grated cheese over onions; add pepper.
Heat soup and milk in same skillet, stirring until smooth.
Pour over onions.
Stir lightly.
Overlap French bread slices in ring on top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until bread is toasted and sauce is bubbly hot.
Serves 4.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Cook sugar, salt, syrup and water until it forms a hard ball in cold water.
Add vinegar and vanilla.
Cook until it reaches crackling stage.
Pour over warm popcorn and form into balls. Place butter on hands to keep from burning hands.

title: easy pumpkin cake
directions: Beat the first 7 ingredients together and pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix over top.
Pour melted oleo over top.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over all.
Bake at 350° for one hour (no longer).
Top with whipped cream.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening together.
Gradually add
the sugars, creaming until mix is light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Stir together dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla to the creamed mixture.
Stir in nuts.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Combine, don't cream, all ingredients.
Put into pie pan. (Keep 1/3 cup of crumbs.)
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Spread 1/3 cup of crumbs on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Cool crumbs and sprinkle on top of pie after it is filled.

title: french dressing
directions: Blend together in blender.

title: pink lozenger cake
directions: Cream together the sugar, butter and vanilla.
Dissolve the lozengers in sweet milk.
The pink mixture is added gradually with the flour and baking powder to creamed batter.
After the batter is entirely smooth, add the beaten whites of four eggs.
Sift flour and baking powder together.

title: chicken marinade(for 6 to 8 chicken breasts.)
directions: Mix ingredients and baste chicken.
Let chicken stand in marinade in refrigerator about 24 hours.
Bake on grill as desired.

title: shrimp monroe
directions: Finely mince green onions.
Saute with sliced mushrooms in butter and garlic.
Add shrimp and cook briefly with vegetables. Blend flour in sherry and add to shrimp mixture, stirring until thickened.
Season with salt and freshly ground pepper.
Just before serving, add sour cream and warm.
Do not boil.
Serve over rice or angel hair pasta.
Thin slightly with milk, if needed. Serves 4.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Bring to a boil all ingredients, except cucumbers or squash, and let cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Slowly add milk, blending thoroughly into mixture.
Fold topping into mixture; pour into prepared crust.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving time and then sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: cherry nut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients in ungreased 9 x 13-inch square pan.
Mix with fork.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool cake and sprinkle with powdered sugar or top with Cool Whip.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as per directions on box.
Pour 1/2 of batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Melt caramels and butter together in double boiler.
Blend in condensed milk.
Remove cake from oven and pour caramel mix over cake. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nut meats.
Pour rest of cake batter over all.
Bake for 30 minutes or until cake is done.
Cut when cool.

title: sloppy joe turnovers
directions: Cook ground beef with onion in a large skillet, stirring continually, until the ground beef is browned and crumbly.
Drain in colander.
Return the ground beef mixture to the skillet.
Stir in ketchup, sour cream, salt and garlic powder.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Pat or roll each biscuit into a 4-inch square on a lightly floured surface.
Arrange the biscuit squares on ungreased baking sheets.
Spoon 1/4 c. of the ground beef mixture in the center of each biscuit square.
Fold over the corner of each square to form a triangle.
Seal edges with a fork.
Cut three 1/2 inch slits in the top of each turnover.
Bake until golden brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Brush with melted butter, if desired.

title: pork chop onion rice bake
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Spread rice in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Reserve 1 tablespoon seasonings from soup mix.
Sprinkle remaining seasonings and onion over rice.
Drain mushrooms reserving liquid.
Place mushrooms and pimento over rice.
Add hot water to reserved mushroom liquid to make 3 cups; pour over rice. Arrange browned chops on top of rice mixture.
Sprinkle chops with remaining seasonings.
Cover tightly with foil and bake at 350° until chops are tender, 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Remove foil and continue cooking for 10 minutes longer until excess liquid evaporates.
Makes 6 servings.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine all liquids. Pour over carrots.
Allow to set overnight in refrigerator. Stir occasionally. Stir again before serving.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil, pudding, 4 eggs and Seven-Up.
Beat until creamy.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 50 minutes in a 300° oven. While cake is baking, mix sugar, margarine, pineapple and juice, 2 eggs and flour in medium saucepan.
Boil for 1 minute.
Add 1 cup coconut, if desired. Pour on cake while it is still hot.

title: squaw corn
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces and fry.
Add corn and salt. Saute until corn is brown.
Add green pepper, sugar and water. Simmer until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pasta with fresh tomato sauce
directions: Heat oil in 1 1/2 to 2-quart pot.
Cook onion and green pepper until tender, but uncolored.
Add tomatoes, salt and honey; cook over moderate heat 15 to 20 minutes until tender but not falling apart.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water and set aside.
Scald milk and add to sugar, Crisco and salt and set aside to cool.
Beat the eggs and add to cooled mixture and 2 cups flour.
Add yeast and 2 to 3 cups more flour.
Let rise once; punch down and let rise again. Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and remove bones.	Place in casserole dish. Combine soups and sour cream.
Spoon the mixture over chicken. Crumble Ritz crackers over casserole.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fudgsicles
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into molds and freeze.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onions; drain off extra liquid. Add eggs, flour, salt and pepper.
Stir to make smooth batter.
Drop spoonful of batter into hot shortening.
Fry until brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Very good with applesauce or sour cream.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat egg whites.
Add small amount of the sugar.
Cream yolks and the remaining sugar.
Beat well with electric mixer. Add vanilla and
cans
evaporated
milk
to
egg white mixture.
Add the
other 1 1/2 cans to yolks.
Combine the two mixtures and
pour	into
freezer
canister.
Add enough whole milk to fill to fill line.	Freeze as usual.

title: teacher appreciation punch
directions: In punch bowl melt sherbet and ice cream.
Add 7-Up, then liquor (if wanted), 1 cup at a time.
Toss in ice cubes as needed (made with 7-Up).

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mash potatoes and mix all of the ingredients together.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream together first four ingredients.
Add eggs and peanut butter; mix well.
Add vanilla.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to mixture; blend well.
Roll into 3/4-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet, one-inch apart.
Press down with fork.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: mandarin orange jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Place in fridge until almost firm.
Add Cool Whip.
Fold into Jell-O until well mixed.
Add drained oranges.
Pour into mold; chill until firm.
Nice side dish for pork or chicken.

title: creamy cinnamon rolls
directions: On a lightly floured surface, roll each of the bread dough loaves to a 12 x 9 inch rectangle. Spread 1/3 c. Eagle Brand over dough rectangles. Sprinkle with 1 c. pecans and cinnamon. Roll up jelly roll style starting from a short side cut. Cut each into 6 slices. Generously grease 13 x 9 inch baking pan. Place rolls, cut side down, in pan. Cover loosely with greased waxed paper and then with plastic wrap. Chill overnight. Cover and chill remaining 1/2 c. Eagle Brand. To bake, let pan of rolls stand at room temperature for 30 minutes. Preheat oven to 350°. Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden brown. Cool in pan 5 minutes; loosen edges and remove rolls from pan.
Meanwhile, for frosting, in small bowl, combine powdered sugar, remaining 1/3 c. Eagle Brand and vanilla. Drizzle frosting on warm rolls. Sprinkle with additional chopped pecans, if desired.

title: stuffed celery
directions: Wash celery.
Cut into serving pieces.
Mix all ingredients well.
Stuff into hollow of celery with knife or fork.
Chill. Serve on relish tray.

title: strawberry glazed cheesecake
directions: In bowl combine crumbs, walnuts and cinnamon.
Add melted butter and mix thoroughly.
Press onto the bottom and 1 1/2 to 2 inches up sides of a spring-form pan.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat 2 minutes; mix all together putting in one egg at a time.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix and form into a ball.

title: pecan squares
directions: Mix until crumbly the cake mix, oil and 1 egg.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican hot dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese products and chips.
Let simmer for 20 minutes to 1 hour or longer (8 to 10 minutes for a microwave).
Add cheese.
Eat with chips.

title: cheese balls
directions: Mix cheese until blended and smooth.
Add all but last 3 ingredients and mix.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Roll into a ball and roll in nuts, paprika and parsley.
Wrap in waxed paper and store in refrigerator.
Serve with crackers.
Delicious.

title: clam fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Drop by spoonfuls into deep hot fat and fry.
When browned, remove and drain.
Serve hot.
Great with clam chowder.

title: modified spinach salad
directions: Mix and chill in refrigerator at least several hours ahead; a day or so is even better.
This dressing keeps for several weeks in refrigerator.

title: wild grits
directions: Add grits to boiling salted water.
Reduce heat and simmer 25 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cool 30 minutes.
Add baking powder, 3/4 cup cheese, onion and pepper.
Mix well. Combine eggs and milk.
Add to cooked grits.
Pour mixture into well-greased 2-quart baking dish. Top with bread crumbs and remaining cheese. Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until browned on top.
Great with chicken or meat dishes.

title: chicken pepper pasta
directions: In skillet, melt margarine.
Blend until sizzling.
Stir in onion, peppers and garlic.
Cook over medium-high heat until peppers are crispy tender.
Remove veggies; set aside.
Reserve juices in pan.
Add chicken, tarragon, salt and pepper.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until chicken is lightly browned and fork-tender.
Prepare vermicelli, drain and add vegetables, half and half, Mozzarella and Parmesan cheese to chicken mixture. Reduce heat and cook until cheeses are melted.
Add vermicelli; toss gently to coat.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Prepare twist pasta as directed.
Drain.
In a bowl, mix cooked pasta, cooked ground beef, pepperoni, spaghetti sauce. Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cheese.
Mix gently. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: In large bowl, layer ingredients as listed.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Toss and serve.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Separate and place crescent rolls flat on an ungreased pizza pan.
Press together as if making a pizza crust.
Crumble and brown sausage; drain.
Sprinkle sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with thawed hash browns, then Cheddar cheese.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients.
Combine the next 6 ingredients.
Pour over the veggies and toss.
Cover and chill 8 to 10 hours.
Drain and serve on lettuce leaves.

title: crock-pot camp stew
directions: Place onion and potatoes in saucepan.
Cover with lightly salted water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer until tender.
Drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients in crock-pot with potatoes and onions.
Cook and simmer on low at least 1 hour.

title: twice baked potato casserole
directions: Spread potatoes in greased shallow casserole dish.
Top with sour cream, cheese, bacon and onions.
Casserole may be covered and refrigerated up to 24 hours, if desired.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until hot.

title: crunchy baked chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Spray baking pan with nonstick cooking spray. Set aside. Place cornflakes in a gallon-size food storage plastic bag. Crush cornflakes by rubbing between palms of hands. Add sesame seeds, paprika, salt and pepper; shake well. Set aside. Dip each chicken breast in milk, then place in bag with cornflake mixture. Shake until coated. Repeat with each chicken breast. Place coated chicken breast in baking pan. Dot evenly with margarine. Bake 30 minutes or until thoroughly cooked.

title: cherry tarts
directions: Combine and chill.
Press into tiny tart pans.
Prick with fork and bake at 350° for 7 minutes.
Prick again and continue baking until light brown.
Cool on rack.
Makes 34 shells.

title: andrew's sausage balls
directions: Let sausage and cheese stand at room temperature.
Mix with Bisquick and sauces.
Form into small balls; place on ungreased pan (not touching) and bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Prepare and cook ahead.
Freeze; reheat.

title: five minute chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat a 9 x 13-inch baking dish with nonstick vegetable spray.
Arrange chicken pieces in baking dish; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients, except paprika, in a large bowl.
Pour mixture over chicken, then bake for 60 to 75 minutes, until done.
Sprinkle with paprika just before serving.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: aunt gracie's brownies
directions: *If not available, use regular cake flour, adding baking powder and salt.

title: cornish hens
directions: Mix in saucepan to taste until margarine is melted.
Add more seasoning, if necessary. Remember to make the sauce a bit strong to give the hens more flavor.
Baste frequently as the hens bake in a 350° oven for approximately 1 hour (longer, if necessary, for the hens to brown).

title: congo bars
directions: Melt sugar and margarine together.
Add 3 beaten eggs.
Stir. Add flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Stir.
Add nuts and chips. Stir.
Batter will be thick.
Spread in a greased and floured 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove promptly and cool 2 hours before cutting in bars.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Pour this over meal mixture in skillet, then add remaining meal mixture.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: christmas candy
directions: Microwave butterscotch and chocolate chips on High for 2 minutes; mix.
Add oil.
Microwave 2 more minutes on High.
Mix in nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: potato casserole
directions: Peel and cut up potatoes.
Cook with chopped onion.
Grate and steam carrots.
Mix potatoes, onion and carrots with rest of ingredients; then bake in a casserole dish at 350° until brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix soda and salt with flour.
Place all ingredients in large bowl.
Mix well.
Form into small balls; flatten with fork.
Cook in a 375° oven until light brown.
Makes approximately 100.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables, celery and onion for 5 minutes (until partially tender) in salt water; drain.
Combine cooked vegetables, mayonnaise and cheese.
Place in casserole dish. Combine crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Stir and mix ingredients thoroughly. Cook on medium-high for 2 minutes. Turn to simmer until ready to use.
Turn heat back on high and thicken with cornstarch.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Make into little balls. Mash thin with a fork after putting on greased cookie sheet.
Cook at 350° until brown.

title: jello mochi
directions: Note:
Instead of microwavable Bundt pan, may use 9-inch round Pyrex pan with Pyrex cup upside down in center.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Combine white bread and broth. Set aside 5 minutes. Cut each oyster into quarters.
Combine all ingredients; spoon into lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Yields 12 servings.

title: chocolate mounds cake
directions: Bake cake as usual.
Mix and melt marshmallows, coconut, sugar and milk on low heat while cake is baking.
Pour mixture over warm cake and put chocolate frosting on immediately while warm.

title: easy holiday punch
directions: Mix
gelatin with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved. Add cold
water and fruit juices.
Pour over ice.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Yields 50 (5 ounce) servings.

title: chicken livers and rice
directions: Sprinkle livers with salt and pepper to taste; shake in small amount of flour in a paper bag.
Brown in butter in hot skillet; place in 6 cup casserole.
Saute onion, celery and rice in remaining butter in skillet until lightly brown.
Add chicken broth; stir well and add parsley.
Pour over livers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed.
Add salt if needed.
Yields 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt and set aside.
Beat together the butter, sugars, vanilla and water until creamy.
Beat in eggs and add flour mixture; mix well. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by spoonfuls onto baking sheet and bake for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hero burgers
directions: Mix well and spread on split buns. Spread well to edges. Broil about 2 minutes, 4-inches from fire.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
For the icing, use powdered sugar and cocoa to taste.
Pour this over hot cake.

title: snack taco dip
directions: Blend with mixer the cream cheese and salsa.
Cut lettuce and tomatoes up in small pieces and layer in 9 x 11-inch pan.
Pour cream cheese mixture over and top with shredded Cheddar cheese. Serve with chips.

title: apple crisp pie
directions: Put pie filling on bottom, next put cake mix (dry), then pecans and melted butter on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sweet cucumber pickles
directions: Dissolve salt in water; pour over cucumbers.
Let stand overnight or approximately 12 hours.
Rinse cucumbers.
Mix and boil sugar, vinegar and 2 cups water.
Drop enough cucumbers for one quart into boiling vinegar.
Let stand until color changes. Pack in jar.
Repeat until all cucumbers are used.
Cover with vinegar mixture and seal.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: potato patties
directions: Use leftover mash potatoes that have been refrigerated.
Add finely chopped onion and paprika.
Form into patties.
Dab butter on each side of the patty and fry in skillet.

title: blueberry loaf
directions: Set the oven at 350°.
Grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
In the bowl of an electric mixer, beat the butter and sugar until fluffy. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add half of the flour mixture to the batter.
Beat just to mix.
Beat in the milk, followed by the remaining flour.
Do not overbeat; it's okay if there are traces of flour in the batter.
Remove the beaters from the bowl and fold in the blueberries with a rubber spatula.
Spoon the batter into the prepared loaf pan, smoothing the top.
Sprinkle the top generously with sugar.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from pan and let cool 10 minutes, then turn over and let cool completely.
Cut into thick slices for serving.

title: crisco pie crust
directions: Mix dry ingredients and Crisco; add water and mix.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven and cookie sheet to 400°.
Thaw pie shell for 10 minutes; prick with fork.
Bake 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce temperature to 350°.
Cook ground beef and onion until brown; drain excess fat.
Add taco seasoning; mix according to directions on package.
Combine beans and 1/3 cup taco sauce in bowl.
Mix well.
Layer half of bean mixture in bottom of crust. Top with half of seasoned meat, 1 cup cheese and nacho chips. Repeat layers, excluding chips.
Bake on preheated cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top with lettuce and tomatoes.
Add taco sauce and sour cream to taste.

title: soft dough clay
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add oil.
Put food color in water and mix with dry ingredients.
Put into pot.
Cook on low fire; watch carefully.
Cook until it becomes thick.
Store in tight sealed plastic bowl.
Fun for children as play dough.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat yolks, sugar and small amount of milk.
Add cocoa, flour, evaporated milk and water.
Cook over low heat until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into 2 baked pie shells (dessert cups for pudding).

title: spicy kraut relish
directions: Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Cover and chill at least 24 hours.
Serve this with bratwurst, smoked sausages or hot dogs.

title: bubble bread
directions: Grease tube pan.
Take one loaf of bread and roll into balls and place in bottom of pan.
Mix together brown sugar, pecans and pudding mix, gradually working in margarine.
Flour 1/2 of this mixture over dough balls.
Repeat with 2nd loaf and cover with remaining mixture.
Let rise to 3/4 top of pan.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: corn spaghetti
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Cook spaghetti in salted water.
When done and drained, add onion-meat mixture and all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Top with grated cheese before baking.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In medium saucepan over medium heat in hot butter or margarine, cook onions until tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper until blended.
Gradually stir in milk and cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add parsley flakes.
In 2-quart casserole, arrange half the potatoes in a layer; pour half the sauce on top and repeat. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain off excess grease.
Add tomato sauce, paste and spices.
Let simmer.
Cook noodles according to box directions.
Place 3 noodles on bottom of pan, then sauce, then 3 cheeses and then repeat.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chess cheese cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, butter and 1 egg and press in 9 x 12-inch buttered pan.
Beat 2 eggs, cream cheese and powdered sugar until creamy and pour over crust mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: prune cake
directions: Sift all dry ingredients together.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour into a greased and floured oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crab salad
directions: Shred crab meat.
Mix together with rest of ingredients.
Add chives, if wanted.

title: pink salad
directions: Cook cranberries in water to cover saucepan until skins pop. Drain and combine with cream cheese, mayonnaise, pineapple, pecans and 1/4 cup sugar in bowl; mix well.
Mix whipping cream, vanilla and 1/4 cup sugar in mixer bowl until soft peaks form.
Fold in salad.
Spoon into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares and serve. Makes 15 servings.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, soda and spices together.
Add alternately with juice.
Use mixer for above.
Add berries by hand.
Bake in three 9-inch cake pans at 350° until brown.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Put sugar, salt and shortening in large bowl.
Pour scalded milk over these ingredients and let stand until warm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add egg to yeast and then to milk mixture. Stir in flour.
Let rise once.
Punch dough down and refrigerate until ready to use.
When ready to use, make in rolls.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes about 30 rolls.

title: corn pudding
directions: (If using whole kernel corn, drain off liquid.)
Mix all ingredients except butter.
Put in casserole dish and put butter on top.
Bake 45 minutes at 400°.

title: 5 hour stew
directions: Cook in large covered pan/pot at 250° for 5 hours. No need to stir.
(May use crock-pot, too.)

title: anise celery
directions: Scrub, remove strings and cut into 4-inch lengths enough celery to tightly pack in a quart fruit jar. Add anise and fill with water. Marinate in refrigerator for a couple of days or until ready to use.

title: terry's chicken barbecue sauce
directions: Melt the margarine; stir in Worcestershire sauce, onion powder and salt.
Then stir in vinegar.
Use this sauce generously to baste your chicken while it is grilling.

title: carne en abobo(guatemala)
directions: Heat oil in a Dutch oven over medium heat.
Saute onion, garlic, and peppers until onion is soft.
Add meat, tomatoes, chilies, spices and beef stock.
(The liquid should cover the meat; if it does not, add a little more beef stock.)
Cover and simmer over low heat until beef is tender (about 2 hours).
Mix masa harina (or cornmeal) with a little bit of cold water.
Stir into the stew and heat until thickened.
(If there is a lot of liquid, you may need to add a bit more thickener.)
Remove the bay leaf, cloves, and any stems from the tomatillos.
Serve the stew on a bed of rice.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook beef cubes until done.
Add base to desired taste.
Add mushrooms and Worcestershire sauce.
Thicken with cornstarch mixed with cold water.
Add sour cream last.
Serve over cooked noodles. Chopped onion is optional.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: In saucepan, lightly brown garlic in butter.
Add water, Worcestershire sauce, liquid smoke, brown sugar, catsup, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: basic microwave meat loaf
directions: Blend ingredients thoroughly and press into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Microwave at 100% on High until internal temperature reaches 150°, approximately 13 to 15 minutes.
Rotate once or twice.
If more moisture is needed, chop small apple or 1/3 cup applesauce will help.
Blend in salt or pepper or peppercorns if desired, before cooking.

title: cheese soup
directions: Saute together the butter, carrots and chives, then add chicken broth and cans of potato soup.
This all needs to simmer for awhile, then add Velveeta (cubed or grated), sour cream and water.
Stir and simmer until cheese is melted and flavors are well blended.
Extra potatoes, broccoli or noodles may also be added now.
This makes a very good Cheese Soup.

title: greek-style meat rolls
directions: Combine beef, 1 cup tomatoes, salt, cumin and pepper in a mixing bowl; mix well.
Shape into two rolls, each about 7 inches long.

title: spaghetti salad(cold)
directions: Mix dressing as directed.
Cook pasta, drain and rinse. Combine with all other ingredients.
Keeps in refrigerator for days.
You may add any combination of other vegetables you wish.

title: green chili cheese bites
directions: Mix together cream cheese, chilies, garlic salt and salsa. Unroll crescent rolls; separate into rectangles.
Press or pinch seams.
Spread mixture on crescent rolls.
Roll and freeze until firm to cut.
Slice about 5 per roll.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 20 minutes.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Put in muffin tin and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: thin layer chocolate cake(ann maloy's)
directions: Bake 10 thin layers for 10 minutes and cool.

title: frozen fruit
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a pan and cook on low heat until thickens. Cool.
Add the pineapple chunks, mandarin oranges, peaches, marshmallows and cherries.
Fold whipped cream into above.
Freeze or refrigerate 12 hours before serving.

title: self-filled cupcakes
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Fill cupcake papers 2/3 full.
Cream the cream cheese with sugar.
Beat in egg and salt. Stir in chocolate chips.
Drop by rounded teaspoon into each cupcake.
Bake as directed on cake mix.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Blend margarine, cheese and flour together.
Make into bite size biscuits.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake on greased cookie sheet 5 minutes at 400°.
Makes approximately 35.

title: yankee pot roast
directions: Trim excess fat from roast; tie if necessary.
In oven going Dutch oven, brown on all sides in hot oil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add sliced celery, onion, sliced carrot, tomatoes, 1/2 cup water and gravy base.
Bake, covered, at 325° for 2 hours.

title: butterscotch pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In medium bowl, beat eggs slightly. Add corn syrup, salt, vanilla, brown sugar and butter.
Mix well. Stir in nuts.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes. Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 30 to 35 minutes or until edge of filling seems set.
Let cool completely on wire rack.
Just before serving, decorate around edge with rosettes of whipped cream.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put cookies in blender.
Cream the cream cheese, butter and sugar.
Set aside.
Blend milk and pudding.
Let set, then fold in Cool Whip.
Then blend in cream cheese mixture.

title: chicken saltimbocca
directions: Rinse chicken and flatten slightly.
Place 1/4 of ham slices and 1 slice of mozzarella cheese on each breast and roll each jelly-roll style, tucking in ends.
Combine remaining ingredients, dampen chicken rolls with a little water, and roll in bread crumb mixture.
Coat well.
Place in baking dish, uncovered, in 350° oven about 30 minutes until chicken is completely done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: microwave peppermint bark
directions: Process peppermint candy in blender or food processor until it is a fine powder and set aside.
Break bark into pieces and place in large microwave-safe bowl.
Microwave at 50% power, uncovered, for 5 to 6 minutes, until bark pieces are soft.
Check and stir after 3 minutes.
Add candy to melted bark and stir well.
Spread onto waxed paper 1/4-inch thick.
Cool until hardened.
You may have to place it in refrigerator.
Break into pieces and store in airtight container.

title: mexican drumsticks
directions: Melt
margarine
and stir in taco mix, salsa, sugar and salt. Roll
each	drumstick in mix and then in the corn chips to coat. Bake in 12-inch Dutch oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Replenish coals if needed.

title: hamburger-vegetable chowder
directions: Brown hamburger in oil over medium heat. Add all other ingredients except rice.
Cook on low for 1 hour, then add rice. Cook until rice is done. Add more water or tomato juice, if it is too thick.
V-8 juice may be substituted for liquid.
Makes 6 servings.
Can be frozen.
I make mine thick.

title: healthy stroganoff
directions: Put water on to boil separately for the noodles.
While it is heating, slice beef into thin strips.
Melt the margarine in a skillet or wok.
Coat the skillet using a pastry brush.
Brown half of the strips at a time for 3 to 4 minutes.
Set aside in a bowl. Saute the mushrooms in the same skillet until tender.
Set the mushrooms aside with the beef strips.
Add the wine, water and bouillon to the skillet.
Bring the mixture to a boil and boil gently for 3 minutes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt butter in large pan.
Mix together flour, sugar, and milk.
Pour over butter.
Put
fruit on top.
Sprinkle with 3/4 cup extra sugar.
Bake one hour at 350 degrees.

title: hidden valley appetizer
directions: Bake 2 crescent roll packages; press in cookie pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes; cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread on cooled crust.
Top with chopped cauliflower, broccoli and green, red and yellow peppers.

title: spinach and bacon quiche
directions: Prebake pie crust about 5 to 10 minutes.
Mix eggs and remaining ingredients.
Whip with wire whisk or mixer until thoroughly mixed.
Pour into prebaked pie crusts.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Done when liquid is on top and pie splits and browns.
It will feel firm.
Makes 2 pies.
One cup ham could be substituted for spinach and bacon.

title: buttercream frosting
directions: Cream part of the sugar into the butter and salt. Add vanilla. Gradually add the rest of the sugar alternating with the milk until desired spreading consistency is reached.

title: gingerbread
directions: Stir flour, soda, spices and salt together.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, beating until light.
Alternately add flour mixture and sour milk.
Beat well after each addition. Pour batter into greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: ham bone soup
directions: Cook beans with ham
bone using all of the water.
Cook until beans are soft.
Add
rest of ingredients.
More ham can be added. Put in jars
and
process
in pressure canner for 1 hour for quarts and 50 minutes for pints.

title: veal roast
directions: Mix together and marinate 1 hour or longer.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until tender.
Baste often.

title: cake mix peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Spread peaches evenly on bottom of pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top of peaches, then sprinkle sugar on cake mix.
Use a fork and lightly mix sugar into cake mix.
Then pour melted butter or margarine evenly on top.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: bread salad
directions: Break the bread into small pieces and place in large bowl. Add other ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve as light lunch or as a salad.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Wash and trim broccoli. Cut off Florets in mixing bowl. Shred stems. Mix all ingredients together.

title: taco chip dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread the cream cheese (after softened), then spread refried beans, then Hormel chili and empty whole bag of cheese over top.
You can microwave until cheese is melted on top or broil in oven for 15 minutes (approximately) until cheese on top is brown. Serve with any type of tortilla chips.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Add all ingredients to cooked and drained ground beef and simmer on low.

title: chili sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cook until done, about 2 hours, on low heat.
Pour into jars while hot and seal.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Combine
flour,
soda, salt and sift; set aside.
Cream sugar, shortening
and
beat
in	egg and vanilla.
Add flour mixture and
mix
well.
Add nuts and make into a roll; chill. Slice and bake at 350° until done.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until creamy, then gradually add sugar.
Beat until stiff, so the mixture stands in peaks.
Stir in chips, nuts and vanilla.
Mix, but do not beat.

title: sour cream honey cookie
directions: Measure liquids together. Same for salt and soda in flour, then put into liquids to mix. (I sour milk day before with vinegar.) I also roll small balls. Roll in sugar. Flatten with fork. Bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes on ungreased pan.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Cook macaroni; shred cheese.
In casserole dish, layer macaroni, cheese, salt and pepper three times.
In small bowl, beat egg and milk; pour over casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes with lid on.
Bake for another 15 minutes with lid off.

title: candied yams
directions: Melt butter in nonstick pan.
Dissolve brown sugar in butter until sticky thick.
Add orange juice and heat through.
If too thick, add some of yam syrup.
Add yams after coating is right. Heat through, approximately 1/2 hour.

title: aunt reba's chocolate cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cream Crisco, margarine and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately.
Beat well.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Blend well.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan at 325° until done, about 1 1/2 hours in my oven.

title: breakfast or midnight snack
directions: Mix cereals thoroughly.
Slice the banana.
Pour on milk. Serves two people.
Can be eaten with coffee and one cup of orange juice.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix Bisquick and cheese and drop on baking sheet.
Melt butter with garlic powder and parsley and brush over the top before and after baking.
Bake at 450° for 9 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients thoroughly. Stir in nuts.
Pour into loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In an 8 x 8-inch square baking dish, put ground meat on bottom. Pour can of soup on top of meat. Pour dissolved bouillon cube over soup. Place Tater Tots on top of soup.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: caramel dip
directions: Mix and serve with fruit (sliced apples, strawberries, grapes, bananas, kiwi, etc.).

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix well; heat slow and cook until thick the milk and cream cheese.
Layer chicken, broccoli and 1/2 the sauce.
Repeat and top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix together the boiling water and jello.
Cool, then add the buttermilk and cranberry sauce.
Mix real good and add nuts or whatever you wish.
Keeps real good.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Combine brown sugar and oil in a large bowl and beat well. Mix buttermilk, egg, vanilla, baking soda and salt in a small bowl.
Add to brown sugar mixture. Blend thoroughly. Gently fold in flour, rhubarb and nuts.
Divide batter evenly between prepared loaf pans.

title: old fashioned apple pie
directions: Line pie pan with crust.
Slice 1/2 stick of oleo on bottom crust.
Mix together sugar and flour and put 1/2 of this mixture over oleo.
Peel and slice enough tart apples to fill bottom crust heaping full.
Cover apples with remaining flour and sugar mixture.
Slice remaining 1/2 stick of oleo over top of sugar and flour.
Cover with pie crust.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 350° and bake for 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Can mix cinnamon with flour and sugar, if desired.
Makes 9-inch pie.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend in blender until thick and smooth.
Makes 1 pint.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cook together juice, eggs, sugar and cornstarch until thick. Cool slightly and add vanilla.
When cold, fold into whipped cream and pour over mixed pineapple, nuts, marshmallows and bananas.

title: crock-pot potato soup
directions: Put all ingredients except evaporated milk into crock-pot. Cook on low 10 to 12 hours (high 3 to 4 hours).
Use mixer to mash ingredients.
Stir in milk during last 1/2 hour.
Serve with bacon bits, croutons and shredded Cheddar cheese.

title: piccalilli relish
directions: Chop the vegetables; cover with salt and let stand overnight. In the morning, drain and press in a cloth to remove all liquid. Add the sugar, vinegar and spices; simmer until clear.
Seal in clean, hot jars.

title: "glorified rice"
directions: Fold rice into whipped cream.
Fold in remaining ingredients. Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with cherries and almond slivers, if desired, or leave plain.
Serves 10.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Finely grate the cheese.
Mash the pimento.
Add mayonnaise and blend thoroughly. Sprinkle with sugar.
Yields 1 1/2 to 2 quarts.

title: chili con queso(mild)
directions: Mix all ingredients in large saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly to avoid scorching.
Cook until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with plain tortilla chips.

title: lattice-topped hamburger pie
directions: In a large skillet cook beef, onion, celery, green pepper and garlic until beef is brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in chili powder and pepper; cook 1 minute.
Add soup and green beans; bring just to boiling.
Turn into an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round baking dish.

title: green beans with almonds and basil
directions: Wash beans and remove strings.
Cover and cook in a small amount of boiling water 10 to 12 minutes or until crisp-tender. Drain well.

title: dinner-in-one(pot, that is)
directions: Brown meat.
Add all in a tightly covered pot.
Bake at 250° for 6 hours.

title: sweet and sour carrots
directions: In a medium saucepan, cook fresh or frozen carrots covered. Cook until tender.
Drain.
Remove from pan.
Mix all together onions, juice, honey, butter, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Cook until tender.

title: plantation pralines
directions: In large pan combine first four ingredients.
Cook on high heat 5 minutes, stirring often.
Add butter and pecans.
Cook for 5 minutes or until soft ball is formed.
Remove from heat and beat until thick.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: hot maple apple cake
directions: Cook apple slices in maple syrup over low heat until tender. Cool. Sift flour, salt, baking powder and spices.
Combine melted butter with water. Stir in dry ingredients and apple mixture.
Mix well, then add beaten egg. Stir lightly to blend.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 11-inch pan. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: peach delight
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Add lemon juice and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Let stand while preparing other ingredients.
Whip cream and add 2 tablespoons sugar and vanilla.
Fold together cake pieces, whipped cream and peaches.

title: mansion punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and jello in the 4 cups of hot water.
Add pineapple juice and cold water to mixture.
Divide into 2 portions and freeze in large plastic containers for 24 hours or longer. Remove from freezer 1 hour prior to serving.
Chop to slushy consistency.
Add ginger ale.
Can be stretched with additional ginger ale.
Yield:
150 (4 ounce) servings.
Variation: Substitute strawberry Kool-Aid and jello.

title: fudge pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs slightly and melt butter. Mix all ingredients together.
Put in an 8 to 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake 25 minutes, or until firm.
Best when served with ice cream!!!

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef in large pot.
Chop onions and add to ground beef.
Add all ingredients.
Cook all ingredients on low temperature for approximately 1 hour.

title: aunt lindy's orange chicken
directions: Brown chicken in 3 tablespoons of butter.
Arrange pieces in casserole dish.
In skillet, lightly saute onion and mushrooms. Stir in bouillon cube and other seasoning and spread over chicken. Bake for 20 minutes at 350 degrees.
Heat remaining butter in skillet, stir in flour and orange juice.
When smooth and thickened pour over chicken and bake an additional 35 minutes, covered.

title: newburg sauce
directions: In saucepan, blend ingredients.
Heat.
Stir occasionally. Makes 1 1/2 cups sauce.
Serve over cooked shrimp.
Add mushrooms and peas, if desired.

title: dessert salad
directions: Mix Jell-O as directed on box; drain pineapple (save juice). Mix pineapple and nuts to Jell-O.
Chill until set.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on box.
Add cream cheese and whip until smooth. Pour over Jell-O.

title: sweet and sour cabbage soup
directions: Put the soup bones in a heavy saucepan.
Add the shredded cabbage and water.
Add the tomatoes, onions, apple and raisins. Add the lemon juice, brown sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: crock-pot beef tips
directions: Cut up beef tips into 1-inch cubes and place in crock-pot. Mix 7-Up with soups and pour over beef.
Cook on low all day (8 to 10 hours).
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cover in foil for first 1/2 hour.

title: home-style vegetable dip
directions: In medium bowl, stir all ingredients together except vegetables.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Serve with vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: italian spaghetti salad
directions: Break spaghetti into thirds and cook according to directions on package.
Run cold water over it to cool.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Beat peanut butter and butter until smooth. Beat in confectioners sugar until combined. Shape into 1-inch balls; place on waxed paper lined baking pan. Refrigerate until peanut butter mixture is firm, approximately 1 hour. In a microwave-safe bowl, melt chocolate chips and oil. Stir well. Dip balls into chocolate. Return to baking sheet. Refrigerate for at least 30 minutes more. Makes 5 dozen.

title: mexican lasagne
directions: Top with shredded lettuce, chopped tomatoes and sour cream.

title: snowballs
directions: Melt margarine with sugar.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Stir. Chill.
Place 1 tablespoon mixture in center of cookie.
Layer cookies and mixture to 4 cookies with cookie on top.
Freeze
2 hours.
After frozen, frost with Cool Whip.
Add coconut and garnish with cherries.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in baking dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Make up Kool-Aid as usual.
Add other ingredients.
Serves 50 to 75.

title: lobster herb sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a small bowl and stir well.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Beat shortening and butter together until smooth, then add all other ingredients together.
Beat until smooth, then add 3 1/2 cups flour.
Add chips and nuts.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes (no longer).

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni as directed; drain.
Rinse with cold water; drain again.
Mix mayonnaise with lemon juice, salt and sugar. Combine with macaroni, celery seed, tomato and celery.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: poppy seed pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Dust with 5 tablespoons sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon.

title: chicken pepperoni parmesan
directions: Mix spaghetti sauce according to package directions.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Top chicken with pepperoni slices.
Pour sauce over pepperoni.
Bake, covered with foil, at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until chicken is tender.
For last 5 to 10 minutes, cover chicken with sliced or grated Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Bake just until cheese begins to melt.
Serve on spaghetti or pasta.

title: wonderful waffles
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Separate yolks and whip whites.
Mix yolks and all other wet ingredients with dry ingredients.
Fold in egg whites.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: In earthenware pan, arrange cucumbers and onions in layers. Sprinkle each layer with salt.
Cover with ice water and let stand 3 hours.
Drain thoroughly.

title: mexican rice
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and bell pepper.
Add rice, tomatoes, tomato sauce, one 6-ounce can of water and Worcestershire sauce. Cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes, or until rice is soft.

title: murgha kari(chicken curry with tomatoes)
directions: Use a casserole or a large skillet with lid.
Cook onions and curry powder in butter for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and salt.
Disjoint and skin chicken; place in sauce.
Cook, uncovered, over medium heat, turning frequently until sauce becomes quite dry and chicken tests done with a fork, about 30 to 40 minutes.
Add hot water; cover pot and cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: ma forrest's pumpkin pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: easy ambrosia
directions: Drain fruit and set aside.
Pour the pudding into the Cool Whip, folding in gently. Fold in fruit cocktail. Ready to serve or chill. Delicious and easy.
Will keep well for a few days, if you wish to prepare
ahead for guests.

title: pumpkin empanadas(bake off winner)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil water with anise seed and cinnamon stick.
Set strained water aside.
In a large mixing bowl, mix 2 1/2 cups flour, 1 cup Crisco, 1/2 teaspoon baking powder, 1/4 cup sugar, 1/4 teaspoon ground cinnamon, 1/4 cup brown sugar and reserved water.
After this is mixed the dough is prepared to make tortillas.
